oj-accordion.name: oj-accordion
oj-accordion.description: An accordion displays a set of collapsible child elements.

expanded.description: A list of expanded child collapsible items.

multiple.description: Specifies whether multiple collapsible items can be open at the same time.

translations.description: A collection of translated resources from the translation bundle, or null if this component has no resources.

refresh.description: Refreshes the visual state of the accordion.

setProperty.description: Sets a property or a single subproperty for complex properties and notifies the component of the change, triggering a corresponding event.

params.name: property
params.description: The property name to set. Supports dot notation for subproperty access.

params.name: value
params.description: The new value to set the property to.

getProperty.description: Retrieves the value of a property or a subproperty.

params.name: property
params.description: The property name to get. Supports dot notation for subproperty access.

setProperties.description: Performs a batch set of properties.

params.name: properties
params.description: An object containing the property and value pairs to set.

ojBeforeExpand.description: Triggered immediately before any collapsible in the accordion is expanded.

ojExpand.description: Triggered after any collapsible in the accordion is expanded.

ojBeforeCollapse.description: Triggered immediately before any collapsible in the accordion is collapsed.

ojCollapse.description: Triggered after any collapsible in the accordion has been collapsed.

slots.description: The <oj-accordion> element accepts one or more <oj-collapsible> elements as children.

contextMenu.description: The contextMenu slot is set on the oj-menu instance within this element. It designates the JET Menu to launch as a context menu.

oj-action-card.name: oj-action-card
oj-action-card.description: An Action Card is an actionable container rendering related information

slots.description: The default slot is the content of the card. The oj-action-card element accepts plain text or DOM nodes as children for the default slot.

ojAction.description: Triggered when the card is clicked, tapped, or upon keyboard ENTER

oj-avatar.name: oj-avatar
oj-avatar.description: An avatar represents a person or entity as initials or an image.

styleClasses.description: Use to display avatar group placeholder image instead of single person placeholder image.

styleClasses.name: oj-avatar-group-image
styleClasses.description: Use to display avatar group placeholder image instead of single person placeholder image.

background.description: Specifies the background of the avatar.

initials.description: Specifies the initials of the avatar.

size.description: Specifies the size of the avatar.

src.description: Specifies the source for the image of the avatar.

oj-bind-dom.name: oj-bind-dom
oj-bind-dom.description: An oj-bind-dom element renders HTML content with access to passed in data properties.

config.description: Configuration object that defines a view and data available to the oj-bind-dom element. The configuration object can be specified directly or via a Promise.

view.description: An array of nodes to be inserted into the DOM. See the Help documenation for more information.

data.description: The data available to the view when expressions are evaluated. Note that the element's binding context will not be made available.

oj-bind-for-each.name: oj-bind-for-each
oj-bind-for-each.description: An oj-bind-for-each binds items of an array to the specified markup section. The markup section is duplicated for each array item when element is rendered.

status.description: Set the alias directly on the template element using the data-oj-as attribute instead.

as.description: An alias for the array item. This is useful if multiple oj-bind-for-each elements are nested to provide access to the data for each iteration level.

data.description: The array or DataProvider that you wish to iterate over. See the Help documentation for more information.

slots.description: The oj-bind-for-each default slot is used to specify the template for binding items of an array if no named slots were defined by the application.

data.description: The current array item being rendered.

index.description: Zero-based index of the current array item being rendered. The index value is not updated in response to array additions and removals and is only recommended for static arrays.

observableIndex.description: An observable that refers to the zero-based index of the current array item being rendered. The observableIndex value is updated in response to array additions and removals and can be used for both static and dynamic arrays.

oj-bind-if.name: oj-bind-if
oj-bind-if.description: An oj-bind-if renders its contents only if a provided test returns true.

test.description: The test condition for the if clause. The children of the element will only be rendered if the test is true.

slots.description: The oj-bind-if default slot is used to specify content that will be rendered when the test condition evaluates to true.

oj-bind-slot.name: oj-bind-slot
oj-bind-slot.description: An oj-bind-slot acts as a placeholder for child DOM to appear in a specified slot.

index.description: An index value allowing the slot children to be individually slotted. This is useful when the composite needs to add additional DOM around slotted children.

name.description: The name of the slot.

slots.description: The oj-bind-slot default slot is used to specify fallback content which will be used in the DOM if the slot has no assigned nodes.

oj-bind-template-slot.name: oj-bind-template-slot
oj-bind-template-slot.description: An oj-bind-template-slot acts as a placeholder for stamped child DOM to appear in a specified slot.

status.description: Set the alias directly on the template element using the data-oj-as attribute instead.

as.description: An optional component-level alias for the context variable that can be referenced inside the default template DOM.

data.description: The object containing additional context variables to extend the stamped template nodes's binding context.

name.description: The name of the slot.

slots.description: The oj-bind-template-slot default slot is used to specify a fallback template that will be used to stamp child DOM if the slot has no assigned template nodes.

oj-bind-text.name: oj-bind-text
oj-bind-text.description: An oj-bind-text binds a text node to an expression.

value.description: The value of the text node.

oj-button.name: oj-button

styleClasses.description: Makes the button small, large, or extra large.
Identifies an action to confirm. Designed for use with a push button.
Draws attention to the button, often identifying the primary action in a set of buttons. Designed for use with a push button. In some themes, this class does nothing.
Allows per-instance control of the focus highlight policy (not typically required). See the Help documentation for more information.

styleClasses.name: button-size
styleClasses.description: Makes the button small, large, or extra large.

styleItems.name: oj-button-sm
styleItems.description: Makes the button small.

styleItems.name: oj-button-lg
styleItems.description: Makes the button large.

styleItems.name: oj-button-xl
styleItems.description: Makes the button extra large.

status.description: This class will be removed in the future.

styleClasses.name: oj-button-confirm
styleClasses.description: Identifies an action to confirm. Designed for use with a push button.

status.description: This class will be removed in the future.

styleClasses.name: oj-button-primary
styleClasses.description: Draws attention to the button, often identifying the primary action in a set of buttons. Designed for use with a push button. In some themes, this class does nothing.

status.description: This class will be removed in the future. Please use 'callToAction' chroming instead.

styleClasses.name: oj-focus-highlight
styleClasses.description: Allows per-instance control of the focus highlight policy (not typically required). See the Help documentation for more information.

oj-button.description: Buttons direct users to initiate or take actions and work with a single tap, click, or keystroke.

chroming.description: Indicates in what states the button has chrome (background and border).

status.description: This value will be removed in the future. Please use solid instead.
This value will be removed in the future. Please use borderless instead.

borderless.description: Borderless buttons are the least prominent variation. Borderless buttons are useful for supplemental actions that require minimal emphasis.

callToAction.description: A Call To Action (CTA) button guides the user to take or complete the action that is the main goal of the page or page section. There should only be one CTA button on a page at any given time.

full.description: Please use solid instead. In typical themes, full-chrome buttons always have chrome.

half.description: In typical themes, half-chrome buttons acquire chrome only in their hover, active, and selected states.

outlined.description: Outlined buttons are salient, but lighter weight than solid buttons. Outlined buttons are useful for secondary actions.

solid.description: Solid buttons stand out, and direct the user's attention to the most important actions in the UI.

disabled.description: Specifies that the button element should be disabled.

display.description: Specifies whether the button displays label and icons, or just icons.

all.description: Display both the label and icons.

translations.description: A collection of translated resources from the translation bundle, or null if this component has no resources.

setProperty.description: Sets a property or a single subproperty for complex properties and notifies the component of the change, triggering a corresponding event.

params.name: property
params.description: The property name to set. Supports dot notation for subproperty access.

params.name: value
params.description: The new value to set the property to.

getProperty.description: Retrieves the value of a property or a subproperty.

params.name: property
params.description: The property name to get. Supports dot notation for subproperty access.

setProperties.description: Performs a batch set of properties.

params.name: properties
params.description: An object containing the property and value pairs to set.

ojAction.description: Triggered when a button is clicked, whether by keyboard, mouse, or touch events. To meet accessibility requirements, the only supported way to react to the click of a button is to listen for this event.

slots.description: The default slot is the button's text label. The oj-button element accepts plain text or DOM nodes as children for the default slot.

contextMenu.description: The contextMenu slot is set on the oj-menu instance within this element. It designates the JET Menu to launch as a context menu.

endIcon.description: The endIcon slot is the button's end icon. The oj-button element accepts DOM nodes as children with the endIcon slot.

startIcon.description: The startIcon slot is the button's start icon. The oj-button element accepts DOM nodes as children with the startIcon slot.

styleClasses.description: Sets button set width to content size.

styleClasses.name: oj-buttonset-width-equal

oj-buttonset-many.description: A buttonset many is a grouping of related buttons where any number of buttons may be selected.

describedBy.description: buttonset's oj-label automatically sets described-by to make it accessible. It is not meant to be set by application developer.

disabled.description: Specifies that the buttonset element should be disabled.

display.description: Specifies whether the buttonset displays label and icons, or just icons.

all.description: Display both the label and icons.

focusManagement.description: Should be set to none when the buttonset is placed within a toolbar.

oneTabstop.description: Focus management is enabled. The Buttonset is a single tabstop with arrow-key navigation.

labelledBy.description: Establishes a relationship between this component and another element, typically an oj-label custom element. See the Help documentation for more information.

translations.description: A collection of translated resources from the translation bundle, or null if this component has no resources.

value.description: Indicates which oj-options in the buttonset are selected.

oj-chart-group.name: oj-chart-group
oj-chart-group.description: The oj-chart-group element is used to declare group properties. See the Help documentation for more information.

drilling.description: Whether drilling is enabled on the group label. See the Help documentation for more information.

labelStyle.description: The CSS style object defining the style of the group label text. See the Help documentation for more information.

name.description: The name of the group.

shortDesc.description: The description of the group. This is used for customizing the tooltip text and only applies to a categorical axis.

oj-chart-item.name: oj-chart-item
oj-chart-item.description: The oj-chart-item element is used to declare item properties. See the Help documentation for more information.

borderColor.description: The border color of the data item. For funnel and pyramid charts, it is used for the slice border.

borderWidth.description: The border width of the data item. For funnel and pyramid charts, it is used for the slice border.

boxPlot.description: An object containing the style properties of the box plot item.

medianSvgClassName.description: The CSS style class to apply to the median line.

medianSvgStyle.description: The CSS inline style to apply to the median line. Only SVG CSS style properties are supported.

q2Color.description: The color of the Q2 segment of the box.

q2SvgClassName.description: The CSS style class to apply to the Q2 segment of the box. See the Help documentation for more information.

q2SvgStyle.description: The CSS inline style to apply to the Q2 segment of the box. See the Help documentation for more information.

q3Color.description: The color of the Q3 segment of the box.

q3SvgClassName.description: The CSS style class to apply to the Q3 segment of the box. See the Help documentation for more information.

q3SvgStyle.description: The CSS inline style to apply to the Q3 segment of the box. See the Help documentation for more information.

whiskerEndLength.description: Specifies the length of the whisker ends in pixels (e.g. '9px') or as a percentage of the box width (e.g. '50%').

whiskerEndSvgClassName.description: The CSS style class to apply to the whisker ends.

whiskerEndSvgStyle.description: The CSS inline style to apply to the whisker ends. Only SVG CSS style properties are supported.

whiskerSvgClassName.description: The CSS style class to apply to the whisker stems.

whiskerSvgStyle.description: The CSS inline style to apply to the whisker stems. Only SVG CSS style properties are supported.

categories.description: An optional array of category strings corresponding to this data item. This enables highlighting and filtering of individual data items through interactions with the legend or other visualization elements. If not defined, series categories are used.

close.description: The close value for stock candlestick. When bar, line, or area series type are used on a stock chart, this value is displayed.

color.description: The color of the data item.

drilling.description: Whether drilling is enabled for the data item. See the Help documentation for more information.

groupId.description: The array of id(s) for the group(s) the item belongs to. For hierarchical groups, it will be an array of outermost to innermost group ids. This is also used to specify the date for non mixed frequency time axes.

high.description: The high value for range bar/area, stock candlestick, or box plot item. Define 'low' and 'high' instead of 'value' or 'y' to create a range bar/area chart.

items.description: An array of nested data items to be used for defining the markers for outliers or additional data items of a box plot.

id.description: The id of the chart item. This id will be provided as part of the context for events on the chart.

items.description: An array of nested data items to be used for defining the markers for outliers or additional data items of a box plot.

x.description: The x value. Mainly used for scatter and bubble chart and to specify the date for mixed-frequency time axis. See the Help documentation for more information.

y.description: The y value. Also the primary value for charts without a y-Axis, such as pie charts.

z.description: The z value. Defines the bubble radius for a bubble chart, as well as the width of a bar or a box plot item.

low.description: The low value for range bar/area, stock candlestick, or box plot item. Define 'low' and 'high' instead of 'value' or 'y' to create a range bar/area chart.

high.description: The high value for range bar/area, stock candlestick, or box plot item. Define 'low' and 'high' instead of 'value' or 'y' to create a range bar/area chart.

open.description: The open value for stock candlestick.

close.description: The close value for stock candlestick. When bar, line, or area series type are used on a stock chart, this value is displayed.

volume.description: The value for stock volume bar. When this value is provided, the volume bar is displayed on the y2 axis.

q1.description: The first quartile value for box plot.

q2.description: The second quartile (median) value for box plot.

q3.description: The third quartile value for box plot.

shortDesc.description: The description of this object. This is used for accessibility and also for customizing the tooltip text.

color.description: The color of the data item.

borderColor.description: The border color of the data item. For funnel and pyramid charts, it is used for the slice border.

borderWidth.description: The border width of the data item. For funnel and pyramid charts, it is used for the slice border.

pattern.description: The pattern used to fill the data item. A solid fill is used by default, unless the seriesEffect is 'pattern'.

svgClassName.description: The CSS style class to apply to the data item. See the Help documentation for more information.

svgStyle.description: The CSS inline style to apply to the data item. See the Help documentation for more information.

markerDisplayed.description: Defines whether the data marker is displayed. Only applies to line, area, scatter, and bubble series. If auto, the markers will be displayed whenever the data points are not connected by a line.

markerShape.description: The shape of the data markers. In addition to the built-in shapes, it may also take SVG path commands to specify a custom shape. See the Help documentation for more information.

markerSize.description: The size of the data markers. Does not apply to bubble charts, which calculate marker size based on the z values.

source.description: The URI of the custom image. If specified, it takes precedence over marker-shape.

sourceHover.description: The optional URI for the hover state. If not specified, the source image will be used.

sourceSelected.description: The optional URI for the selected state. If not specified, the source image will be used.

sourceHoverSelected.description: The optional URI for the hover selected state. If not specified, the source image will be used.

label.description: The label for the data item. For range series, if an array of two values is provided, the first and second value will apply to the low and high point respectively. Not supported for box plot or candlestick.

labelPosition.description: The position of the data label. For range series, if an array of two values is provided, the first and second value will apply to the low and high point respectively. See the Help documentation for more information.

labelStyle.description: The CSS style object defining the style of the data label. See the Help documentation for more information.

categories.description: An optional array of category strings corresponding to this data item. This enables highlighting and filtering of individual data items through interactions with the legend or other visualization elements. If not defined, series categories are used.

value.description: The value for this data item. Corresponding to the y value for bar, line, area, and combo charts and the slice values for pie, funnel and pyramid charts. Null can be specified to skip a data point.

targetValue.description: The target value for a funnel chart. When this is set, the value attribute defines the filled area within the slice and this represents the value of the whole slice.

drilling.description: Whether drilling is enabled for the data item. See the Help documentation for more information.

boxPlot.description: An object containing the style properties of the box plot item.

medianSvgClassName.description: The CSS style class to apply to the median line.

medianSvgStyle.description: The CSS inline style to apply to the median line. Only SVG CSS style properties are supported.

q2Color.description: The color of the Q2 segment of the box.

q2SvgClassName.description: The CSS style class to apply to the Q2 segment of the box. See the Help documentation for more information.

q2SvgStyle.description: The CSS inline style to apply to the Q2 segment of the box. See the Help documentation for more information.

q3Color.description: The color of the Q3 segment of the box.

q3SvgClassName.description: The CSS style class to apply to the Q3 segment of the box. See the Help documentation for more information.

q3SvgStyle.description: The CSS inline style to apply to the Q3 segment of the box. See the Help documentation for more information.

whiskerEndLength.description: Specifies the length of the whisker ends in pixels (e.g. '9px') or as a percentage of the box width (e.g. '50%').

whiskerEndSvgClassName.description: The CSS style class to apply to the whisker ends.

whiskerEndSvgStyle.description: The CSS inline style to apply to the whisker ends. Only SVG CSS style properties are supported.

whiskerSvgClassName.description: The CSS style class to apply to the whisker stems.

whiskerSvgStyle.description: The CSS inline style to apply to the whisker stems. Only SVG CSS style properties are supported.

labelPosition.description: The position of the data label. For range series, if an array of two values is provided, the first and second value will apply to the low and high point respectively. See the Help documentation for more information.

labelStyle.description: The CSS style object defining the style of the data label. See the Help documentation for more information.

low.description: The low value for range bar/area, stock candlestick, or box plot item. Define 'low' and 'high' instead of 'value' or 'y' to create a range bar/area chart.

markerDisplayed.description: Defines whether the data marker is displayed. Only applies to line, area, scatter, and bubble series. If auto, the markers will be displayed whenever the data points are not connected by a line.

markerShape.description: The shape of the data markers. In addition to the built-in shapes, it may also take SVG path commands to specify a custom shape. See the Help documentation for more information.

markerSize.description: The size of the data markers. Does not apply to bubble charts, which calculate marker size based on the z values.

open.description: The open value for stock candlestick.

pattern.description: The pattern used to fill the data item. A solid fill is used by default, unless the seriesEffect is 'pattern'.

q1.description: The first quartile value for box plot.

q2.description: The second quartile (median) value for box plot.

q3.description: The third quartile value for box plot.

seriesId.description: The id for the series the item belongs to.

shortDesc.description: The description of this object. This is used for accessibility and also for customizing the tooltip text.

source.description: The URI of the custom image. If specified, it takes precedence over marker-shape.

sourceHover.description: The optional URI for the hover state. If not specified, the source image will be used.

sourceHoverSelected.description: The optional URI for the hover selected state. If not specified, the source image will be used.

sourceSelected.description: The optional URI for the selected state. If not specified, the source image will be used.

svgClassName.description: The CSS style class to apply to the data item. See the Help documentation for more information.

svgStyle.description: The CSS inline style to apply to the data item. See the Help documentation for more information.

targetValue.description: The target value for a funnel chart. When this is set, the value attribute defines the filled area within the slice and this represents the value of the whole slice.

value.description: The value for this data item. Corresponding to the y value for bar, line, area, and combo charts and the slice values for pie, funnel and pyramid charts. Null can be specified to skip a data point.

volume.description: The value for stock volume bar. When this value is provided, the volume bar is displayed on the y2 axis.

x.description: The x value. Mainly used for scatter and bubble chart and to specify the date for mixed-frequency time axis. See the Help documentation for more information.

y.description: The y value. Also the primary value for charts without a y-Axis, such as pie charts.

z.description: The z value. Defines the bubble radius for a bubble chart, as well as the width of a bar or a box plot item.

oj-chart-series.name: oj-chart-series
oj-chart-series.description: The oj-chart-series element is used to declare series properties. See the Help documentation for more information.

areaColor.description: The area color of the series. Only applies if series type is area or lineWithArea.

areaSvgClassName.description: The CSS style class to apply if series type is area or lineWithArea. See the Help documentation for more information.

areaSvgStyle.description: The inline style to apply if series type is area or lineWithArea. See the Help documentation for more information.

assignedToY2.description: Defines whether the series is associated with the y2 axis. Only applies to Cartesian bar, line, area, and combo charts.

borderColor.description: The border color of the series.

borderWidth.description: The border width of the series.

boxPlot.description: An object containing the style properties of the box plot series.

medianSvgClassName.description: The CSS style class to apply to the median line.

medianSvgStyle.description: The CSS inline style to apply to the median line. Only SVG CSS style properties are supported.

q2Color.description: The color of the Q2 segment of the box.

q2SvgClassName.description: The CSS style class to apply to the Q2 segment of the box. See the Help documentation for more information.

q2SvgStyle.description: The CSS inline style to apply to the Q2 segment of the box. See the Help documentation for more information.

q3Color.description: The color of the Q3 segment of the box.

q3SvgClassName.description: The CSS style class to apply to the Q3 segment of the box. See the Help documentation for more information.

q3SvgStyle.description: The CSS inline style to apply to the Q3 segment of the box. See the Help documentation for more information.

whiskerEndLength.description: Specifies the length of the whisker ends in pixels (e.g. '9px') or as a percentage of the box width (e.g. '50%').

whiskerEndSvgClassName.description: The CSS style class to apply to the whisker ends.

whiskerEndSvgStyle.description: The CSS inline style to apply to the whisker ends. Only SVG CSS style properties are supported.

whiskerSvgClassName.description: The CSS style class to apply to the whisker stems.

whiskerSvgStyle.description: The CSS inline style to apply to the whisker stems. Only SVG CSS style properties are supported.

categories.description: An optional array of category strings corresponding to this series. This allows highlighting and filtering of a series through interactions with legend sections. If not defined, the series id is used.

color.description: The color of the series.

displayInLegend.description: Defines whether the series should be shown in the legend. When set to 'auto', the series will not be displayed in the legend if it has null data or if it is a stock, funnel, or pyramid series.

drilling.description: Whether drilling is enabled on the series item. See the Help documentation for more information.

lineStyle.description: The line style of the data line. Only applies to line, lineWithArea, scatter, and bubble series.

lineType.description: The line type of the data line or area. Only applies to line, area, scatter, and bubble series. See the Help documentation for more information.

lineWidth.description: The width of the data line. Only applies to line, lineWithArea, scatter, and bubble series.

markerColor.description: The color of the data markers, if different from the series color.

markerDisplayed.description: Defines whether the data marker is displayed. Only applies to line, area, scatter, and bubble series. See the Help documentation for more information.

markerShape.description: The shape of the data markers. In addition to the built-in shapes, it may also take SVG path commands to specify a custom shape. See the Help documentation for more information.

markerSize.description: The size of the data markers.

markerSvgClassName.description: The CSS style class to apply to the data markers. See the Help documentation for more information.

markerSvgStyle.description: The inline style to apply to the data markers. See the Help documentation for more information.

name.description: The name of the series, displayed in the legend and tooltips.

pattern.description: The pattern used to fill the series. A solid fill is used by default, unless the seriesEffect is 'pattern'.

pieSliceExplode.description: A number from 0 to 1 indicating the amount to explode the pie slice. Only applies to pie charts.

shortDesc.description: The description of this series. This is used for accessibility and for customizing the tooltip text on the corresponding legend item for the series.

source.description: The URI of the custom image. If specified, it takes precedence over shape.

sourceHover.description: The optional URI for the hover state. If not specified, the source image will be used.

sourceHoverSelected.description: The optional URI for the hover selected state. If not specified, the source image will be used.

sourceSelected.description: The optional URI for the selected state. If not specified, the source image will be used.

stackCategory.description: In stacked charts, groups series together for stacking. All series without a stackCategory will be assigned to the same stack.

svgClassName.description: The CSS style class to apply to the series. For series of type lineWithArea, this style will only be applied to the line if areaSvgClassName is also specified. See the Help documentation for more information.

svgStyle.description: The inline style to apply to the series. For series of type lineWithArea, this style will only be applied to the line if areaSvgStyle is also specified. See the Help documentation for more information.

type.description: The type of data objects to display for this series. Only applies to bar, line, area, stock, box plot, and combo charts.

oj-chart.name: oj-chart
oj-chart.description: A chart displays information graphically, making relationships among the data easier to understand.

animationOnDataChange.description: Defines the animation that is applied on data changes. Animation is automatically disabled when there are a large number of data items.

animationOnDisplay.description: Defines the animation that is shown on initial display. Animation is automatically disabled when there are a large number of data items.

status.description: Set the alias directly on the template element using the data-oj-as attribute instead.

as.description: An alias for the '$current' context variable passed to slot content for the itemTemplate, seriesTemplate, or groupTemplate slots.

coordinateSystem.description: The coordinate system of the chart. Only applies to bar, line, area, combo, scatter, and bubble charts.

data.description: An object defining the series and groups, when using a DataProvider to populate the chart data. Also accepts a Promise for deferred data rendering.

dataCursor.description: Defines whether the data cursor is enabled. The data cursor is not supported for polar charts. See the Help documentation for more information.

dataCursorBehavior.description: Defines the behavior of the data cursor when moving between data items.

dataCursorPosition.description: Specifies the position of the data cursor. Used for synchronizing data cursors across multiple charts. Null if the data cursor is not displayed.

x.description: The x value of the data cursor.

y.description: The y value of the data cursor. If both y and y2 are defined, y will take precedence.

y2.description: The y2 value of the data cursor. If both y and y2 are defined, y will take precedence.

dataLabel.description: A function that returns a custom data label. The function takes a context argument, provided by the chart. See the Help documentation for more information.

dnd.description: Provides support for HTML5 Drag and Drop events. See the Help documentation for more information.

drag.description: An object that describes drag functionality.

groups.description: Allows dragging of chart groups from the categorical axis labels.

dataTypes.description: The MIME types to use for the dragged data in the dataTransfer object. This can be a string if there is only one type, or an array of strings if multiple types are needed.

drag.description: An optional callback function that receives the "drag" event as argument.

dragEnd.description: An optional callback function that receives the "dragend" event as argument.

dragStart.description: An optional callback function that receives the "dragstart" event and context information as arguments. See the Help documentation for more information.

items.description: Allows dragging of chart data items, including bars, line/area/scatter markers, bubbles, and pie/funnel/pyramid slices.

dataTypes.description: The MIME types to use for the dragged data in the dataTransfer object. This can be a string if there is only one type, or an array of strings if multiple types are needed.

drag.description: An optional callback function that receives the "drag" event as argument.

dragEnd.description: An optional callback function that receives the "dragend" event as argument.

dragStart.description: An optional callback function that receives the "dragstart" event and context information as arguments. See the Help documentation for more information.

series.description: Allows dragging of chart series from the legend items.

dataTypes.description: The MIME types to use for the dragged data in the dataTransfer object. This can be a string if there is only one type, or an array of strings if multiple types are needed.

drag.description: An optional callback function that receives the "drag" event as argument.

dragEnd.description: An optional callback function that receives the "dragend" event as argument.

dragStart.description: An optional callback function that receives the "dragstart" event and context information as arguments. See the Help documentation for more information.

drop.description: An object that describes drop functionality.

dataTypes.description: An array of MIME data types this element can accept. This property is required unless dragEnter, dragOver, and drop callback functions are specified to handle the corresponding events.

dragEnter.description: An optional callback function that receives the "dragenter" event and empty context information as arguments. See the Help documentation for more information.

dragLeave.description: An optional callback function that receives the "dragleave" event and empty context information as arguments.

dragOver.description: An optional callback function that receives the "dragover" event and empty context information as arguments. See the Help documentation for more information.

drop.description: An optional callback function that receives the "drop" event and empty context information as arguments. See the Help documentation for more information.

plotArea.description: Allows dropping on the plot area.

dataTypes.description: An array of MIME data types this element can accept. This property is required unless dragEnter, dragOver, and drop callback functions are specified to handle the corresponding events.

dragEnter.description: An optional callback function that receives the "dragenter" event and context information as arguments. See the Help documentation for more information.

dragLeave.description: An optional callback function that receives the "dragleave" event and context information as arguments. See the Help documentation for more information.

dragOver.description: An optional callback function that receives the "dragover" event and context information as arguments. See the Help documentation for more information.

drop.description: An optional callback function that receives the "drop" event and context information as arguments. See the Help documentation for more information.

xAxis.description: Allows dropping on the X axis.

dataTypes.description: An array of MIME data types this element can accept. This property is required unless dragEnter, dragOver, and drop callback functions are specified to handle the corresponding events.

dragEnter.description: An optional callback function that receives the "dragenter" event and context information as arguments. See the Help documentation for more information.

dragLeave.description: An optional callback function that receives the "dragleave" event and context information as arguments. See the Help documentation for more information.

dragOver.description: An optional callback function that receives the "dragover" event and context information as arguments. See the Help documentation for more information.

drop.description: An optional callback function that receives the "drop" event and context information as arguments. See the Help documentation for more information.

y2Axis.description: Allows dropping on the Y2 axis.

dataTypes.description: An array of MIME data types this element can accept. This property is required unless dragEnter, dragOver, and drop callback functions are specified to handle the corresponding events.

dragEnter.description: An optional callback function that receives the "dragenter" event and context information as arguments. See the Help documentation for more information.

dragLeave.description: An optional callback function that receives the "dragleave" event and context information as arguments. See the Help documentation for more information.

dragOver.description: An optional callback function that receives the "dragover" event and context information as arguments. See the Help documentation for more information.

drop.description: An optional callback function that receives the "drop" event and context information as arguments. See the Help documentation for more information.

yAxis.description: Allows dropping on the Y axis.

dataTypes.description: An array of MIME data types this element can accept. This property is required unless dragEnter, dragOver, and drop callback functions are specified to handle the corresponding events.

dragEnter.description: An optional callback function that receives the "dragenter" event and context information as arguments. See the Help documentation for more information.

dragLeave.description: An optional callback function that receives the "dragleave" event and context information as arguments. See the Help documentation for more information.

dragOver.description: An optional callback function that receives the "dragover" event and context information as arguments. See the Help documentation for more information.

drop.description: An optional callback function that receives the "drop" event and context information as arguments. See the Help documentation for more information.

dragMode.description: The action that is performed when a drag occurs on the chart. See the Help documentation for more information.

drilling.description: Specifies whether drilling is enabled. Drillable objects will show a pointer cursor on hover and fire an ojDrill event on click (double click if selection is enabled). See the Help documentation for more information.

groupComparator.description: A comparator function that determines the ordering of the chart groups when using a DataProvider. If undefined, the group will follow the order in which they are found in the data.

groups.description: An array of strings identifying the group labels, or an array of objects specifying group labels and styles. See the Help documentation for more information.

id.description: The id of the group. Defaults to the name if not specified. This is also used to specify the date for non mixed frequency time axes.

groups.description: An array of nested group objects.

drilling.description: Whether drilling is enabled on the group label. See the Help documentation for more information.

labelStyle.description: The CSS style object defining the style of the group label text. See the Help documentation for more information.

name.description: The name of the group.

shortDesc.description: The description of the group. This is used for customizing the tooltip text and only applies to a categorical axis.

hiddenCategories.description: An array of category strings used for filtering. Series or data items with any category matching an item in this array will be filtered.

hideAndShowBehavior.description: Defines the hide and show behavior that is performed when clicking on a legend item. When data items are hidden, the y axes can be optionally rescaled to fit to the remaining data.

highlightMatch.description: The matching condition for the highlightedCategories property. See the Help documentation for more information.

highlightedCategories.description: An array of category strings used for highlighting. Series or data items matching categories in this array will be highlighted.

hoverBehavior.description: Defines the behavior applied when hovering over data items.

initialZooming.description: Specifies whether automatic initial zooming is enabled. Only applies to bar, line, area, and combo charts with zoomAndScroll turned on. See the Help documentation for more information.

legend.description: An object defining the style, positioning, and behavior of the legend.

backgroundColor.description: The color of the legend background.

borderColor.description: The border color of the legend.

maxSize.description: Defines the maximum size of the legend in pixels (e.g. '50px') or percent (e.g. '15%').

position.description: The position of the legend within the chart. By default, the legend will be placed on the side or bottom, based on the size of the chart and the legend contents.

referenceObjectSection.description: An object defining the reference object section in the legend.

title.description: The title of the reference object section.

titleHalign.description: The horizontal alignment of the section title. If the section is collapsible or nested, only start alignment is supported.

titleStyle.description: The CSS style object defining the style of the section title.

rendered.description: Defines whether the legend is displayed. If set to auto, the legend will be hidden for charts with a large number of series. See the Help documentation for more information.

scrolling.description: Defines whether scrolling is enabled for the legend.

sections.description: An array of objects defining the additional legend sections, other than the default series and reference object sections.

items.description: An array of objects with the following properties defining the legend items. Also accepts a Promise for deferred data rendering. No data will be rendered if the Promise is rejected.

borderColor.description: The border color of the marker. Only applies if symbolType is "marker" or "lineWithMarker".

categories.description: An array of categories for the legend item. Legend items currently only support a single category. If no category is specified, this defaults to the id or text of the legend item.

categoryVisibility.description: Defines whether the legend item corresponds to visible data items. A hollow symbol is shown if the value is "hidden".

color.description: The color of the legend symbol (line or marker). When symbolType is "lineWithMarker", this attribute defines the line color and the markerColor attribute defines the marker color.

id.description: The id of the legend item, which is provided as part of the context for events fired by the legend. If not specified, the default depends upon whether a DataProvider is being used.

lineStyle.description: The line style. Only applies when the symbolType is "line" or "lineWithMarker".

lineWidth.description: The line width in pixels. Only applies when the symbolType is "line" or "lineWithMarker".

markerColor.description: The color of the marker, if different than the line color. Only applies if the symbolType is "lineWithMarker".

markerShape.description: The shape of the marker. Only applies if symbolType is "marker" or "lineWithMarker". Can take the name of a built-in shape or the SVG path commands for a custom shape. Does not apply if a custom image is specified.

pattern.description: The pattern used to fill the marker. Only applies if symbolType is "marker" or "lineWithMarker".

shortDesc.description: The description of this legend item. This is used for accessibility and for customizing the tooltip text.

source.description: The URI of the image of the legend symbol.

symbolType.description: The type of legend symbol to display.

sections.description: An array of nested legend sections.

title.description: The title of the legend section.

titleHalign.description: The horizontal alignment of the section title. If the section is collapsible or nested, only start alignment is supported.

titleStyle.description: The CSS style object defining the style of the section title. The following style properties are supported: color, cursor, fontFamily, fontSize, fontStyle, fontWeight, textDecoration.

seriesSection.description: An object defining the series section in the legend.

title.description: The title of the series section.

titleHalign.description: The horizontal alignment of the section title. If the section is collapsible or nested, only start alignment is supported.

titleStyle.description: The CSS style object defining the style of the section title.

size.description: Defines the size of the legend in pixels (e.g. '50px') or percent (e.g. '15%').

symbolHeight.description: The height of the legend symbol (line or marker) in pixels.

symbolWidth.description: The width of the legend symbol (line or marker) in pixels.

textStyle.description: The CSS style object defining the style of the legend text.

titleHalign.description: The horizontal alignment of the title.

titleStyle.description: The CSS style object defining the style of the title.

orientation.description: The chart orientation. Only applies to bar, line, area, combo, box plot, and funnel charts.

otherThreshold.description: Specifies the fraction of the whole pie under which a slice would be aggregated into an "Other" slice. Valid values range from 0 (default) to 1. For example, a value of 0.1 would cause all slices which are less than 10% of the pie to be aggregated into the "Other" slice. Only applies to pie chart.

overview.description: An object defining the overview scrollbar. Only applies if zoomAndScroll is not off. Currently only supported for vertical bar, line, area, stock, and combo charts.

content.description: An object containing the property override for the overview chart. See the Help documentation for more information.

height.description: Specifies the height of the overview scrollbar in pixels (e.g. '50px') or percent (e.g. '15%').

rendered.description: Specifies whether the overview scrollbar is rendered. If not, simple scrollbar will be used.

pieCenter.description: An object defining the center content of a pie chart. Either a label can be displayed at the center of the pie chart or custom HTML content.

converter.description: The converter to format the label if it is numeric. See the Help documentation for more information.

label.description: Specifies the text for the label. When a innerRadius is specified, the label will automatically be scaled to fit within the inner circle. If the innerRadius is 0, the default font size will be used.

labelStyle.description: The CSS style object defining the style of the label.

renderer.description: A function that returns custom center content. The function takes a context argument, provided by the chart. See the Help documentation for more information.

scaling.description: The scaling behavior of the label if it is numeric. When using a converter, scaling should be set to none, as the formatted result may not be compatible with the scaling suffixes.

plotArea.description: An object defining the style of the plot area.

backgroundColor.description: The color of the plot area background.

borderColor.description: The border color to be set on the chart's plot area.

borderWidth.description: The border width to be set on the chart's plot area.

rendered.description: Specifies whether the plot area is rendered.

polarGridShape.description: Defines whether the grid shape of the polar chart is circle or polygon. Only applies to polar line and area charts.

selection.description: An array used to define the ids of the initially selected objects. See the Help documentation for more information.

selectionMode.description: The type of selection behavior that is enabled on the chart. See the Help documentation for more information.

multiple.description: Multiple items can be selected at the same time.

none.description: Selection is disabled.

single.description: Only a single item can be selected at a time.

series.description: An array of objects defining series labels and override series styles. See the Help documentation for more information.

id.description: The id of the series. Defaults to the name or the series index if not specified.

items.description: An array of values or an array of objects that defines the data items for the series.

id.description: The id of the chart item. This id will be provided as part of the context for events on the chart.

items.description: An array of nested data items to be used for defining the markers for outliers or additional data items of a box plot.

x.description: The x value. Mainly used for scatter and bubble chart and to specify the date for mixed-frequency time axis. See the Help documentation for more information.

y.description: The y value. Also the primary value for charts without a y-Axis, such as pie charts.

z.description: The z value. Defines the bubble radius for a bubble chart, as well as the width of a bar or a box plot item.

low.description: The low value for range bar/area, stock candlestick, or box plot item. Define 'low' and 'high' instead of 'value' or 'y' to create a range bar/area chart.

high.description: The high value for range bar/area, stock candlestick, or box plot item. Define 'low' and 'high' instead of 'value' or 'y' to create a range bar/area chart.

open.description: The open value for stock candlestick.

close.description: The close value for stock candlestick. When bar, line, or area series type are used on a stock chart, this value is displayed.

volume.description: The value for stock volume bar. When this value is provided, the volume bar is displayed on the y2 axis.

q1.description: The first quartile value for box plot.

q2.description: The second quartile (median) value for box plot.

q3.description: The third quartile value for box plot.

shortDesc.description: The description of this object. This is used for accessibility and also for customizing the tooltip text.

color.description: The color of the data item.

borderColor.description: The border color of the data item. For funnel and pyramid charts, it is used for the slice border.

borderWidth.description: The border width of the data item. For funnel and pyramid charts, it is used for the slice border.

pattern.description: The pattern used to fill the data item. A solid fill is used by default, unless the seriesEffect is 'pattern'.

svgClassName.description: The CSS style class to apply to the data item. See the Help documentation for more information.

svgStyle.description: The CSS inline style to apply to the data item. See the Help documentation for more information.

markerDisplayed.description: Defines whether the data marker is displayed. Only applies to line, area, scatter, and bubble series. If auto, the markers will be displayed whenever the data points are not connected by a line.

markerShape.description: The shape of the data markers. In addition to the built-in shapes, it may also take SVG path commands to specify a custom shape. See the Help documentation for more information.

markerSize.description: The size of the data markers. Does not apply to bubble charts, which calculate marker size based on the z values.

source.description: The URI of the custom image. If specified, it takes precedence over marker-shape.

sourceHover.description: The optional URI for the hover state. If not specified, the source image will be used.

sourceSelected.description: The optional URI for the selected state. If not specified, the source image will be used.

sourceHoverSelected.description: The optional URI for the hover selected state. If not specified, the source image will be used.

label.description: The label for the data item. For range series, if an array of two values is provided, the first and second value will apply to the low and high point respectively. Not supported for box plot or candlestick.

labelPosition.description: The position of the data label. For range series, if an array of two values is provided, the first and second value will apply to the low and high point respectively. See the Help documentation for more information.

labelStyle.description: The CSS style object defining the style of the data label. See the Help documentation for more information.

categories.description: An optional array of category strings corresponding to this data item. This enables highlighting and filtering of individual data items through interactions with the legend or other visualization elements. If not defined, series categories are used.

value.description: The value for this data item. Corresponding to the y value for bar, line, area, and combo charts and the slice values for pie, funnel and pyramid charts. Null can be specified to skip a data point.

targetValue.description: The target value for a funnel chart. When this is set, the value attribute defines the filled area within the slice and this represents the value of the whole slice.

drilling.description: Whether drilling is enabled for the data item. See the Help documentation for more information.

boxPlot.description: An object containing the style properties of the box plot item.

medianSvgClassName.description: The CSS style class to apply to the median line.

medianSvgStyle.description: The CSS inline style to apply to the median line. Only SVG CSS style properties are supported.

q2Color.description: The color of the Q2 segment of the box.

q2SvgClassName.description: The CSS style class to apply to the Q2 segment of the box. See the Help documentation for more information.

q2SvgStyle.description: The CSS inline style to apply to the Q2 segment of the box. See the Help documentation for more information.

q3Color.description: The color of the Q3 segment of the box.

q3SvgClassName.description: The CSS style class to apply to the Q3 segment of the box. See the Help documentation for more information.

q3SvgStyle.description: The CSS inline style to apply to the Q3 segment of the box. See the Help documentation for more information.

whiskerEndLength.description: Specifies the length of the whisker ends in pixels (e.g. '9px') or as a percentage of the box width (e.g. '50%').

whiskerEndSvgClassName.description: The CSS style class to apply to the whisker ends.

whiskerEndSvgStyle.description: The CSS inline style to apply to the whisker ends. Only SVG CSS style properties are supported.

whiskerSvgClassName.description: The CSS style class to apply to the whisker stems.

whiskerSvgStyle.description: The CSS inline style to apply to the whisker stems. Only SVG CSS style properties are supported.

areaColor.description: The area color of the series. Only applies if series type is area or lineWithArea.

areaSvgClassName.description: The CSS style class to apply if series type is area or lineWithArea. See the Help documentation for more information.

areaSvgStyle.description: The inline style to apply if series type is area or lineWithArea. See the Help documentation for more information.

assignedToY2.description: Defines whether the series is associated with the y2 axis. Only applies to Cartesian bar, line, area, and combo charts.

borderColor.description: The border color of the series.

borderWidth.description: The border width of the series.

boxPlot.description: An object containing the style properties of the box plot series.

medianSvgClassName.description: The CSS style class to apply to the median line.

medianSvgStyle.description: The CSS inline style to apply to the median line. Only SVG CSS style properties are supported.

q2Color.description: The color of the Q2 segment of the box.

q2SvgClassName.description: The CSS style class to apply to the Q2 segment of the box. See the Help documentation for more information.

q2SvgStyle.description: The CSS inline style to apply to the Q2 segment of the box. See the Help documentation for more information.

q3Color.description: The color of the Q3 segment of the box.

q3SvgClassName.description: The CSS style class to apply to the Q3 segment of the box. See the Help documentation for more information.

q3SvgStyle.description: The CSS inline style to apply to the Q3 segment of the box. See the Help documentation for more information.

whiskerEndLength.description: Specifies the length of the whisker ends in pixels (e.g. '9px') or as a percentage of the box width (e.g. '50%').

whiskerEndSvgClassName.description: The CSS style class to apply to the whisker ends.

whiskerEndSvgStyle.description: The CSS inline style to apply to the whisker ends. Only SVG CSS style properties are supported.

whiskerSvgClassName.description: The CSS style class to apply to the whisker stems.

whiskerSvgStyle.description: The CSS inline style to apply to the whisker stems. Only SVG CSS style properties are supported.

categories.description: An optional array of category strings corresponding to this series. This allows highlighting and filtering of a series through interactions with legend sections. If not defined, the series id is used.

color.description: The color of the series.

displayInLegend.description: Defines whether the series should be shown in the legend. When set to 'auto', the series will not be displayed in the legend if it has null data or if it is a stock, funnel, or pyramid series.

drilling.description: Whether drilling is enabled on the series item. See the Help documentation for more information.

lineStyle.description: The line style of the data line. Only applies to line, lineWithArea, scatter, and bubble series.

lineType.description: The line type of the data line or area. Only applies to line, area, scatter, and bubble series. See the Help documentation for more information.

lineWidth.description: The width of the data line. Only applies to line, lineWithArea, scatter, and bubble series.

markerColor.description: The color of the data markers, if different from the series color.

markerDisplayed.description: Defines whether the data marker is displayed. Only applies to line, area, scatter, and bubble series. See the Help documentation for more information.

markerShape.description: The shape of the data markers. In addition to the built-in shapes, it may also take SVG path commands to specify a custom shape. See the Help documentation for more information.

markerSize.description: The size of the data markers.

markerSvgClassName.description: The CSS style class to apply to the data markers. See the Help documentation for more information.

markerSvgStyle.description: The inline style to apply to the data markers. See the Help documentation for more information.

name.description: The name of the series, displayed in the legend and tooltips.

pattern.description: The pattern used to fill the series. A solid fill is used by default, unless the seriesEffect is 'pattern'.

pieSliceExplode.description: A number from 0 to 1 indicating the amount to explode the pie slice. Only applies to pie charts.

shortDesc.description: The description of this series. This is used for accessibility and for customizing the tooltip text on the corresponding legend item for the series.

source.description: The URI of the custom image. If specified, it takes precedence over shape.

sourceHover.description: The optional URI for the hover state. If not specified, the source image will be used.

sourceHoverSelected.description: The optional URI for the hover selected state. If not specified, the source image will be used.

sourceSelected.description: The optional URI for the selected state. If not specified, the source image will be used.

stackCategory.description: In stacked charts, groups series together for stacking. All series without a stackCategory will be assigned to the same stack.

svgClassName.description: The CSS style class to apply to the series. For series of type lineWithArea, this style will only be applied to the line if areaSvgClassName is also specified. See the Help documentation for more information.

svgStyle.description: The inline style to apply to the series. For series of type lineWithArea, this style will only be applied to the line if areaSvgStyle is also specified. See the Help documentation for more information.

type.description: The type of data objects to display for this series. Only applies to bar, line, area, stock, box plot, and combo charts.

seriesComparator.description: A comparator function that determines the ordering of the chart series when using a DataProvider. If undefined, the series will follow the order in which they are found in the data.

sorting.description: Specifies the sorting of the data. It should only be used for pie charts, bar/line/area charts with one series, or stacked bar/area charts. Sorting will not apply when using a hierarchical group axis.

splitDualY.description: Defines whether the plot area is split into two sections, so that sets of data assigned to the different Y-axes appear in different parts of the plot area. Stock charts do not support "off".

splitterPosition.description: In a split dual-Y chart, specifies the fraction of the space that is given to the Y-axis subchart. Valid values are numbers from 0 to 1.

stack.description: Defines whether the data items are stacked. Only applies to bar, line, area, and combo charts. Does not apply to range series.

stackLabel.description: Defines whether the total values of stacked data items should be displayed. Only applies to bar charts. See the Help documentation for more information.

styleDefaults.description: An object defining the default styles for series colors, marker shapes, and other style attributes. Properties specified on this object may be overridden by specifications on the data object.

animationDownColor.description: The color of the indicator shown for a decreasing data change animation.

animationDuration.description: The duration of the animations in milliseconds.

animationIndicators.description: Defines whether data change indicators are displayed during animation.

animationUpColor.description: The color of the indicator shown for an increasing data change animation.

barGapRatio.description: Specifies the width of the bar group gap as a ratio of the group width. The valid value is a number from 0 to 1.

borderColor.description: The default border color for the data items. For funnel and pyramid charts, it is used for the slice border.

borderWidth.description: The default border width for the data items. For funnel and pyramid charts, it is used for the slice border.

boxPlot.description: An object containing the style properties of the box plot items.

medianSvgClassName.description: The CSS style class to apply to the median line.

medianSvgStyle.description: The CSS inline style to apply to the median line. Only SVG CSS style properties are supported.

whiskerEndLength.description: Specifies the length of the whisker ends in pixels (e.g. '9px') or as a percentage of the box width (e.g. '50%').

whiskerEndSvgClassName.description: The CSS style class to apply to the whisker ends.

whiskerEndSvgStyle.description: The CSS inline style to apply to the whisker ends.

whiskerSvgClassName.description: The CSS style class to apply to the whisker stems.

whiskerSvgStyle.description: The CSS inline style to apply to the whisker stems.

colors.description: The array defining the default color ramp for the series.

dataCursor.description: An object defining the data cursor style.

lineColor.description: The color of the data cursor line.

lineStyle.description: The line style of the data cursor line.

lineWidth.description: The width of the data cursor line in pixels.

markerColor.description: The color of the data cursor marker. Defaults to the data series color.

markerDisplayed.description: Whether the data cursor marker is displayed. Marker should only be hidden if the data cursor is displaying information for the entire group.

markerSize.description: The size of the data cursor marker in pixels.

dataItemGaps.description: Specifies the presence and size of the gaps between data items, such as bars, markers, and areas. Valid values are a percentage string from 0% to 100%, where 100% produces the maximum supported gaps.

dataLabelCollision.description: Rule for adjusting data label layout. See the Help documentation for more information.

dataLabelPosition.description: The position of the data label. For range series, if an array of two values is provided, the first and second value will apply to the low and high point respectively. See the Help documentation for more information.

dataLabelStyle.description: The CSS style object defining the style of the data label. See the Help documentation for more information.

funnelBackgroundColor.description: The default background color of funnel slices that show actual/target values.

groupSeparators.description: An object defining the style for hierarchical label separators.

color.description: The color of the separators lines.

rendered.description: Defines whether the group separators are displayed.

hoverBehaviorDelay.description: Specifies initial hover delay in milliseconds for highlighting items in chart.

lineStyle.description: The line style of the data line. Only applies to line, lineWithArea, scatter, and bubble series.

lineType.description: The line type of the data line or area. Only applies to line, area, scatter, and bubble series. See the Help documentation for more information.

lineWidth.description: The width of the data line. Only applies to line, lineWithArea, scatter, and bubble series.

markerColor.description: The color of the data markers, if different from the series color.

markerDisplayed.description: Defines whether the data markers should be displayed. Only applies to line, area, scatter, and bubble series. If auto, the markers will be displayed whenever the data points are not connected by a line.

markerShape.description: The shape of the data markers. In addition to the built-in shapes, it may also take SVG path commands to specify a custom shape. See the Help documentation for more information.

markerSize.description: The size of the data markers in pixels.

marqueeBorderColor.description: The border color of the marquee. Applies to marquee selection and marquee zoom.

marqueeColor.description: The fill color of the marquee. Applies to marquee selection and marquee zoom.

maxBarWidth.description: Specifies the maximum width of each bar in pixels.

otherColor.description: Specifies the color of the "Other" slice. Only applies to pie chart.

patterns.description: The array defining the default pattern ramp for the series. This is used only when seriesEffect is 'pattern'.

pieFeelerColor.description: The color of the line extending from the pie slice to the slice label.

pieInnerRadius.description: Specifies the radius of the inner circle that can be used to create a donut chart. Valid values range from 0 (default) to 1. Not supported if 3D effect is on.

selectionEffect.description: The selection effect that is applied to selected items. The values explode and highlightAndExplode only apply to pie charts.

seriesEffect.description: Defines the fill effect for the data items.

shapes.description: The array defining the default shape ramp for the series. Valid values are defined in the markerShape attribute.

stackLabelStyle.description: The CSS style object defining the style of the stack label.

stockFallingColor.description: In stock charts, the color of the candlestick when the 'open' value is greater than the 'close' value.

stockRangeColor.description: In stock charts, the color of the range bars for candlestick.

stockRisingColor.description: In stock charts, the color of the candlestick when the 'close' value is greater than the 'open' value.

stockVolumeColor.description: In stock charts, the color of the volume bars. If specified, overrides the default rising and falling colors used by the volume bars.

threeDEffect.description: Defines whether the chart is displayed with a 3D effect. Only applies to pie, funnel and pyramid charts.

tooltipLabelStyle.description: The CSS style object defining the style of the labels in the tooltip.

tooltipValueStyle.description: The CSS style object defining the style of the values in the tooltip.

timeAxisType.description: The type of time axis to display in the chart. Time axis is only supported for Cartesian bar, line, area, stock, box plot, and combo charts. See the Help documentation for more information.

tooltip.description: An object containing an optional callback function for tooltip customization.

renderer.description: A function that returns a custom tooltip for chart. The function takes a context argument, provided by the chart. See the Help documentation for more information.

touchResponse.description: Specifies configuration options for touch and hold delays on mobile devices. See the Help documentation for more information.

trackResize.description: Defines whether the element will automatically render in response to changes in size. See the Help documentation for more information.

translations.description: A collection of translated resources from the translation bundle, or null if this component has no resources.

componentName.description: Used to describe the data visualization type for accessibility.

labelAndValue.description: Used to display a label and its value.

labelClearSelection.description: Text shown for clearing multiple selection on touch devices.

labelClose.description: Used for the close value in the tooltip for stock data.

labelCountWithTotal.description: Used to display a count out of a total.

labelDataVisualization.description: Label for data visualizations used for accessibility.

labelDate.description: Used for the date value in the tooltip, if a time axis is being used.

labelDefaultGroupName.description: Used when the group names are not specified.

labelHigh.description: >Used for the high value in the tooltip for stock and range data.

labelInvalidData.description: Text shown when the component receives invalid data.

labelLow.description: Used for the low value in the tooltip for stock and range data.

labelNoData.description: Text shown when the component receives no data.

labelOpen.description: Used for the open value in the tooltip for stock data.

labelOther.description: Used for the other series label which aggregates small data values.

labelPercentage.description: Used for displaying the percentage in the tooltip.

labelQ1.description: Used for displaying the first quartile for box plots.

labelQ2.description: Used for displaying the second quartile (i.e. median) for box plots.

labelQ3.description: Used for displaying the third quartile for box plots.

labelTargetValue.description: Used for the funnel chart target value.

labelValue.description: Used for the data item value in the tooltip.

labelVolume.description: Used for the volume value in the tooltip for stock data.

labelX.description: Used for the x value in the tooltip.

labelY.description: Used for the y value in the tooltip.

labelZ.description: Used for the z value in the tooltip.

stateCollapsed.description: Used to describe the collapsed state for accessibility.

stateDrillable.description: Used to describe a drillable object for accessibility.

stateExpanded.description: Used to describe the expanded state for accessibility.

stateHidden.description: Used to describe the hidden state for accessibility.

stateIsolated.description: Used to describe the isolated state for accessibility.

stateMaximized.description: Used to describe the maximized state for accessibility.

stateMinimized.description: Used to describe the minimized state for accessibility.

stateSelected.description: Used to describe the selected state for accessibility.

stateUnselected.description: Used to describe the unselected state for accessibility.

stateVisible.description: Used to describe the visible state for accessibility.

tooltipSelect.description: Used for the marquee select tooltip.

tooltipZoom.description: Used for the marquee zoom tooltip.

type.description: Specifies the chart type. See the Help documentation for more information.

valueFormats.description: An object specifying value formatting and tooltip behavior, whose keys generally correspond to the attribute names on the data items.

close.description: Specifies the value formatting and tooltip behavior for the close values of a stock chart.

scaling.description: The scaling behavior of the value. When using a converter, scaling should be set to none, as the formatted result may not be compatible with the scaling suffixes.

tooltipLabel.description: A string representing the label that is displayed before the value in the tooltip.
