xAxis.description: An object defining properties for the axis, tick marks, tick labels, and axis titles.

axisLine.description: An object defining properties for the axis line.

lineColor.description: The color of the axis line.

lineWidth.description: The width of the axis line.

rendered.description: Defines whether the axis line is rendered.

baselineScaling.description: Defines whether the axis baseline starts at the minimum value of the data or at zero. Only applies to numerical data axes.

dataMax.description: The maximum data value corresponding to an axis. If specified, the automatic axis extent calculation will use this value. Only applies to numerical axes.

dataMin.description: The minimum data value corresponding to an axis. If specified, the automatic axis extent calculation will use this value. Only applies to numerical axes.

majorTick.description: An object defining properties for the major tick marks.

baselineColor.description: The color of the major tick mark at the baseline (x = 0). Valid values are auto, inherit, or a custom color. If set to inherit, it will follow the lineColor attribute.

baselineStyle.description: The line style of the major tick mark at the baseline (x = 0). If not specified, it will follow the lineStyle attribute.

baselineWidth.description: The width of the major tick mark at the baseline (x = 0) If not specified, it will follow the lineWidth attribute.

lineColor.description: The color of the major tick marks.

lineStyle.description: The line style of the major tick marks.

lineWidth.description: The width of the major tick marks.

rendered.description: Defines whether the major tick marks are rendered.

max.description: The maximum value of the axis. Defaults to null for automatic calculation based on the data. See the Help documentation for more information.

maxSize.description: Defines the maximum size of the axis in pixels (e.g. '50px') or percent (e.g. '15%').

min.description: The minimum value of the axis. Defaults to null for automatic calculation based on the data. See the Help documentation for more information.

minStep.description: The minimum increment between major tick marks. This is typically used to prevent fractional axis values for discrete measures. Only applies to numerical axes.

minorStep.description: The increment between minor tick marks. Defaults to null for automatic calculation based on the data. Only applies to numerical axes. See the Help documentation for more information.

minorTick.description: An object defining properties for the minor tick marks.

lineColor.description: The color of the minor tick marks.

lineStyle.description: The line style of the minor tick marks.

lineWidth.description: The width of the minor tick marks.

rendered.description: Defines whether the minor tick marks are rendered.

referenceObjects.description: The array of reference objects associated with the axis.

categories.description: An optional array of category strings corresponding to this reference object. This allows highlighting and filtering of a reference object through interactions with legend sections. If not defined, the reference object id is used.

color.description: The color of the reference object.

displayInLegend.description: Defines whether the reference object should be shown in the legend.

high.description: The high value of an area reference object. See the Help documentation for more information.

id.description: The id of the reference object.

lineStyle.description: The line style of the line reference object. Does not apply to area reference objects.

lineWidth.description: The width of the line reference object. Does not apply to area reference objects.

location.description: The location of the reference object relative to the data items.

low.description: The low value of an area reference object. See the Help documentation for more information.

shortDesc.description: The description of this object. This is used for accessibility and also for customizing the tooltip text.

svgClassName.description: The CSS style class to apply to the reference object. See the Help documentation for more Information.

svgStyle.description: The CSS inline style to apply to the reference object. See the Help documentation for more Information.

text.description: The text displayed in the legend for the reference object.

type.description: The type of reference object being shown. See the Help documentation for more information.

value.description: The value of a line reference object. This property defines a constant value across the entire reference object. See the Help documentation for more information.

rendered.description: Defines whether the axis is rendered.

scale.description: Defines the axis scale. Only applies to numerical axes.

size.description: Defines the size of the axis in pixels (e.g. '50px') or percent (e.g. '15%').

step.description: The increment between major tick marks. Defaults to null for automatic calculation based on the data. Only applies to time and numerical axes. See the Help documentation for more information.

tickLabel.description: An object defining the properties of the tick labels.

converter.description: The converter used to format the labels. See the Help documentation for more information.

rendered.description: Defines whether the tick labels are rendered.

rotation.description: Defines whether the chart will automatically rotate the labels by 90 degrees in order to fit more labels on the axis. The rotation will only be applied to categorical labels for a horizontal axis.

scaling.description: The scaling behavior of the labels. When using a converter, scaling should be set to none, as the formatted result may not be compatible with the scaling suffixes.

style.description: The CSS style object defining the style of the labels.

title.description: The axis title. Does not apply to polar charts.

titleStyle.description: The CSS style object defining the style of the axis title.

viewportEndGroup.description: Specifies the end group of the current viewport. Only applies to charts with group or time axis. If not specified, the default end group is the last group in the data set.

viewportMax.description: Specifies the maximum x coordinate of the current viewport for zoom and scroll. See the Help documentation for more information.

viewportMin.description: Specifies the minimum x coordinate of the current viewport for zoom and scroll. See the Help documentation for more information.

viewportStartGroup.description: Specifies the start group of the current viewport. Only applies to charts with group or time axis. If not specified, the default start group is the first group in the data set.

minStep.description: The minimum increment between major tick marks. This is typically used to prevent fractional axis values for discrete measures.

minorStep.description: The increment between minor tick marks. Defaults to null for automatic calculation based on the data. See the Help documentation for more information.

minorTick.description: An object defining properties for the minor tick marks.

lineColor.description: The color of the minor tick marks.

lineStyle.description: The line style of the minor tick marks.

lineWidth.description: The width of the minor tick marks.

rendered.description: Defines whether the minor tick marks are rendered.

position.description: The position of the axis relative to its content. For vertical charts, only start and end apply. For horizontal charts, only top and bottom apply.

referenceObjects.description: The array of reference objects associated with the axis.

categories.description: An optional array of category strings corresponding to this reference object. This allows highlighting and filtering of a reference object through interactions with legend sections. If not defined, the reference object id is used.

color.description: The color of the reference object.

displayInLegend.description: Defines whether the reference object should be shown in the legend.

high.description: The high value of an area reference object. This property defines a constant value across the entire reference area. See the Help documentation for more information.

id.description: The id of the reference object.

items.description: An array of values or an array of objects that define the data for a varying reference object. See the Help documentation for more information.

high.description: The high value of this point of a varying area reference object.

low.description: The low value of this point of a varying area reference object.

value.description: The value of this point of a varying line reference object. Null can be specified to skip a data point.

x.description: The x value of this point. Mainly used for scatter and bubble charts, and to specify the date for mixed-frequency time axis. See the Help documentation for more information.

lineStyle.description: The line style of the line reference area. Does not apply to area reference objects.

lineType.description: The line type of the varying reference object. See the Help documentation for more information.

lineWidth.description: The width of the line reference object. Does not apply to area reference objects.

location.description: The location of the reference object relative to the data items.

low.description: The low value of an area reference object. This property defines a constant value across the entire reference area. See the Help documentation for more information.

shortDesc.description: The description of this object. This is used for accessibility and also for customizing the tooltip text.

svgClassName.description: The CSS style class to apply to the reference object. See the Help documentation for more Information.

svgStyle.description: The CSS inline style to apply to the reference object. See the Help documentation for more Information.

text.description: The text displayed in the legend for the reference object.

type.description: The type of reference object being shown. See the Help documentation for more information.

value.description: The value of a line reference object. This property defines a constant value across the entire reference object. See the Help documentation for more information.

rendered.description: Defines whether the axis is rendered.

scale.description: Defines the axis scale. Only applies to numerical axes.

size.description: Defines the size of the axis in pixels (e.g. '50px') or percent (e.g. '15%').

step.description: The increment between major tick marks. Defaults to null for automatic calculation based on the data. See the Help documentation for more information.

tickLabel.description: An object defining the properties of the tick labels.

converter.description: The converter used to format the labels. See the Help documentation for more information.

position.description: Defines the position of the tick labels relative to the plot area. Inside position is not supported for scatter and bubble charts.

rendered.description: Defines whether the tick labels are rendered.

scaling.description: The scaling behavior of the labels. When using a converter, scaling should be set to none, as the formatted result may not be compatible with the scaling suffixes.

style.description: The CSS style object defining the style of the labels.

title.description: The axis title. Does not apply to polar charts.

titleStyle.description: The CSS style object defining the style of the axis title.

viewportMax.description: Specifies the maximum y coordinate of the current viewport for zoom and scroll. Only applies to bubble and scatter charts. If not specified, this value will be the axis max.

viewportMin.description: Specifies the minimum y coordinate of the current viewport for zoom and scroll. Only applies to bubble and scatter charts. If not specified, this value will be the axis min.

zoomAndScroll.description: Specifies the zoom and scroll behavior of the chart. See the Help documentation for more information.

zoomDirection.description: Specifies the zoom direction of bubble and scatter charts. "Auto" zooms in both x and y direction. Use "x" or "y" for single direction zooming.

x.description: The x value. Mainly used for scatter and bubble chart and to specify the date for mixed-frequency time axis. See the Help documentation for more information.

y.description: The y value. Also the primary value for charts without a y-Axis, such as pie charts.

z.description: The z value. Defines the bubble radius for a bubble chart, as well as the width of a bar or a box plot item.

low.description: The low value for range bar/area, stock candlestick, or box plot item. Define 'low' and 'high' instead of 'value' or 'y' to create a range bar/area chart.

high.description: The high value for range bar/area, stock candlestick, or box plot item. Define 'low' and 'high' instead of 'value' or 'y' to create a range bar/area chart.

open.description: The open value for stock candlestick.

close.description: The close value for stock candlestick. When bar, line, or area series type are used on a stock chart, this value is displayed.

volume.description: The value for stock volume bar. When this value is provided, the volume bar is displayed on the y2 axis.

q1.description: The first quartile value for box plot.

q2.description: The second quartile (median) value for box plot.

q3.description: The third quartile value for box plot.

shortDesc.description: The description of this object. This is used for accessibility and also for customizing the tooltip text.

color.description: The color of the data item.

borderColor.description: The border color of the data item. For funnel and pyramid charts, it is used for the slice border.

borderWidth.description: The border width of the data item. For funnel and pyramid charts, it is used for the slice border.

pattern.description: The pattern used to fill the data item. A solid fill is used by default, unless the seriesEffect is 'pattern'.

svgClassName.description: The CSS style class to apply to the data item. See the Help documentation for more information.

svgStyle.description: The CSS inline style to apply to the data item. See the Help documentation for more information.

markerDisplayed.description: Defines whether the data marker is displayed. Only applies to line, area, scatter, and bubble series. If auto, the markers will be displayed whenever the data points are not connected by a line.

markerShape.description: The shape of the data markers. In addition to the built-in shapes, it may also take SVG path commands to specify a custom shape. See the Help documentation for more information.

markerSize.description: The size of the data markers. Does not apply to bubble charts, which calculate marker size based on the z values.

source.description: The URI of the custom image. If specified, it takes precedence over marker-shape.

sourceHover.description: The optional URI for the hover state. If not specified, the source image will be used.

sourceSelected.description: The optional URI for the selected state. If not specified, the source image will be used.

sourceHoverSelected.description: The optional URI for the hover selected state. If not specified, the source image will be used.

label.description: The label for the data item. For range series, if an array of two values is provided, the first and second value will apply to the low and high point respectively. Not supported for box plot or candlestick.

labelPosition.description: The position of the data label. For range series, if an array of two values is provided, the first and second value will apply to the low and high point respectively. See the Help documentation for more information.

labelStyle.description: The CSS style object defining the style of the data label. See the Help documentation for more information.

value.description: The value for this data item. Corresponding to the y value for bar, line, area, and combo charts and the slice values for pie, funnel and pyramid charts. Null can be specified to skip a data point.

targetValue.description: The target value for a funnel chart. When this is set, the value attribute defines the filled area within the slice and this represents the value of the whole slice.

drilling.description: Whether drilling is enabled for the data item. See the Help documentation for more information.

boxPlot.description: An object containing the style properties of the box plot item.

medianSvgClassName.description: The CSS style class to apply to the median line.

medianSvgStyle.description: The CSS inline style to apply to the median line. Only SVG CSS style properties are supported.

q2Color.description: The color of the Q2 segment of the box.

q2SvgClassName.description: The CSS style class to apply to the Q2 segment of the box. See the Help documentation for more information.

q2SvgStyle.description: The CSS inline style to apply to the Q2 segment of the box. See the Help documentation for more information.

q3Color.description: The color of the Q3 segment of the box.

q3SvgStyle.description: The CSS inline style to apply to the Q3 segment of the box. See the Help documentation for more information.

categories.description: An optional array of category strings corresponding to this series. This allows highlighting and filtering of a series through interactions with legend sections. If not defined, the series id is used.

color.description: The color of the series.

drilling.description: Whether drilling is enabled on the series item. See the Help documentation for more information.

lineStyle.description: The line style of the data line. Only applies to line, lineWithArea, scatter, and bubble series.

lineType.description: The line type of the data line or area. Only applies to line, area, scatter, and bubble series. See the Help documentation for more information.

lineWidth.description: The width of the data line. Only applies to line, lineWithArea, scatter, and bubble series.

markerColor.description: The color of the data markers, if different from the series color.

markerDisplayed.description: Defines whether the data marker is displayed. Only applies to line, area, scatter, and bubble series. See the Help documentation for more information.

markerShape.description: The shape of the data markers. In addition to the built-in shapes, it may also take SVG path commands to specify a custom shape. See the Help documentation for more information.

markerSize.description: The size of the data markers.

markerSvgClassName.description: The CSS style class to apply to the data markers. See the Help documentation for more information.

markerSvgStyle.description: The inline style to apply to the data markers. See the Help documentation for more information.

name.description: The name of the series, displayed in the legend and tooltips.

pattern.description: The pattern used to fill the series. A solid fill is used by default, unless the seriesEffect is 'pattern'.

sourceHover.description: The optional URI for the hover state. If not specified, the source image will be used.

svgClassName.description: The CSS style class to apply to the series. For series of type lineWithArea, this style will only be applied to the line if areaSvgClassName is also specified. See the Help documentation for more information.

scrollPolicy.description: Specifies how data are fetched as user scrolls through the data grid.

auto.description: the DataGrid will decide the scroll policy

loadMoreOnScroll.description: additional data are fetched when the user scrolls to the bottom of the DataGrid and all previous data are kept in the DOM.

scroll.description: virtual scrolling is used meaning only rows/columns visible in the viewport are fetched and kept in the DOM

scrollPolicyOptions.description: Specifies fetch options for scrolling behaviors that trigger data fetches.

maxColumnCount.description: The maximum number of columns to display before fetching more data rows will be stopped.

maxRowCount.description: The maximum number of rows to display before fetching more data rows will be stopped.

scrollPosition.description: Specifies the current scroll position of the data grid. See the Help documentation for more information.

x.description: the horizontal position in pixel

y.description: the vertical position in pixel

rowIndex.description: the zero-based row index of the cell at the origin of the grid. If scrollPolicy is set to 'loadMoreOnScroll' and the index is greater than maxCount set in scrollPolicyOptions, then it will scroll and fetch until the end of the list is reached and there's no more items to fetch.

columnIndex.description: the zero-based column index of the cell at the origin of the grid. If scrollPolicy is set to 'loadMoreOnScroll' and the index is greater than maxCount set in scrollPolicyOptions, then it will scroll and fetch until the end of the list is reached and there's no more items to fetch.

rowKey.description: the row key of the cell at the origin of the grid. If DataGridDataSource is used for data and the key does not exist in the DataGridDataSource, then the value is ignored. If it is unknown in the data source then the grid will fetch and scroll until the item is found or the end of the axis is reached and there's no more items to fetch.

columnKey.description: the column key of the cell at the origin of the grid. If DataGridDataSource is used for data and the key does not exist in the DataGridDataSource, then the value is ignored. If it is unknown in the data source then the grid will fetch and scroll until the item is found or the end of the axis is reached and there's no more items to fetch.

offsetX.description: the horizontal offset in pixel relative to the cell identified by key/index.

offsetY.description: the vertical offset in pixel relative to the cell identified by key/index.

selectionMode.description: Specifies the row and cell selection modes. See the Help documentation for more information.

cell.description: Specifies the cell selection mode. By default, cell selection is disabled.

multiple.description: Multiple cells can be selected at the same time.

none.description: Selection is disabled.

single.description: Only a single cell can be selected at a time.

row.description: Specifies the row selection mode. By default, row selection is disabled.

multiple.description: Multiple rows can be selected at the same time.

none.description: Selection is disabled.

single.description: Only a single row can be selected at a time.

translations.description: A collection of translated resources from the translation bundle, or null if this component has no resources.

accessibleRangeSelectModeOn.description: Provides properties to customize the accessible context for discontinuous selection on.

accessibleRowContext.description: Provides properties to customize the accessible context for the row index.

accessibleRowEndHeaderContext.description: Provides properties to customize the accessible context for the row end header index.

accessibleRowEndHeaderLabelContext.description: Provides properties to customize the accessible context for the row end header label.

accessibleRowExpanded.description: Provides properties to customize the accessible context when a row is expanded.

accessibleRowHeaderLabelContext.description: Provides properties to customize the accessible context for the row header label.

accessibleRowSelected.description: Provides properties to customize the accessible context when a row is selected.

accessibleRowSpanContext.description: Provides properties to customize the accessible context for the cell extent/span.

accessibleSelectionAffordanceBottom.description: Provides properties to customize the accessible context for the bottom selection affordance on touch device.

accessibleSelectionAffordanceTop.description: Provides properties to customize the accessible context for the top selection affordance on touch devices.

accessibleSortAscending.description: Provides properties to customize the accessible text when a header is sorted ascending.

accessibleSortDescending.description: Provides properties to customize the accessible text when a header is sorted descending.

accessibleStateSelected.description: Provides properties to customize the accessible context when an item has been selected.

accessibleSummaryEstimate.description: Provides properties to customize the accessible context read when the exact row and column count are unknown.

accessibleSummaryExact.description: Provides properties to customize the accessible context read when the exact row and column count are known.

accessibleSummaryExpanded.description: Provides properties to customize the accessible context reading out the total number of rows expanded inside the data grid.

oj-file-picker.name: oj-file-picker
oj-file-picker.description: A file picker displays a clickable dropzone for selecting files from the device storage.

Apply to the dropzone of the file picker.

implementation.description: Specifies an implementation-specific default as the preferred facing mode

messages.description: Messages that should be displayed to the user (e.g. in an oj-messages component) describing invalid files.

until.description: This property may be populated with a Promise to provide short-term feedback during a user interaction (typically drag and drop); the feedback should be cleared upon the resolution of this Promise.

ojSelect.description: Triggered after the files are selected

files.description: The files that were just selected.

oj-film-strip.name: oj-film-strip
oj-film-strip.description: A filmstrip lays out its children in a single row or column across logical pages and allows navigating through them.

arrowPlacement.description: Specifies the placement of the navigation arrows.

adjacent.description: Arrows are outside, adjacent to the filmStrip content. The arrows are still inside the bounds of the filmStrip element itself.

overlay.description: Arrows are inside, overlaying the filmStrip content.

arrowVisibility.description: Specifies the visibility of the navigation arrows.

auto.description: Behaves as if the value were visible when the arrow-placement attribute is set to adjacent, and hover when the arrow-placement attribute is set to overlay.

hover.description: Arrows are visible when the mouse is over the filmStrip, and hidden otherwise.

currentItem.description: Specifies the child item whose logical page should be displayed.

id.description: string id of the item

index.description: numeric 0-based index of the item

off.description: Navigation is bounded between first and last page and can't go any further in the direction of navigation.

page.description: Navigation is not bounded between first and last page and can go further in the direction of navigation. This lets the user loop around from first page to last page, or from last page to first page.

maxItemsPerPage.description: Specifies the maximum number of child items shown in a logical page.

orientation.description: Specifies the orientation of the FilmStrip.

translations.description: A collection of translated resources from the translation bundle, or null if this component has no resources.

labelAccArrowNextPage.description: Accessible label for the next page navigation arrow.

labelAccArrowPreviousPage.description: Accessible label for the previous page navigation arrow.

labelAccFilmStrip.description: Accessible page information label for the filmstrip element.

tipArrowNextPage.description: Tooltip for the next page navigation arrow.

tipArrowPreviousPage.description: Tooltip for the previous page navigation arrow.

refresh.description: Refreshes the visual state of the FilmStrip.

getItemsPerPage.description: Get the actual number of items shown per logical page.

getPagingModel.description: Get the PagingModel created and used by the FilmStrip.

oj-form-layout.name: oj-form-layout

styleClasses.description: In Redwood by default a form layout has a max width, add this class if you'd like to opt out and have the form layout to stretch the full width.

styleClasses.name: oj-formlayout-full-width
styleClasses.description: In Redwood by default a form layout has a max width, add this class if you'd like to opt out and have the form layout to stretch the full width.

oj-form-layout.description: A form layout manages the layout of labels and fields in a form.

colspanWrap.description: Specifies how to fit components with colspan attribute in the form layout, when there are fewer columns left in the current row than the colspan value specifies.

nowrap.description: The component will occupy the remaining columns in the current row.

wrap.description: The component will start from the first column of the next row.

direction.description: Specifies the layout direction of the form layout children.

column.description: Components are laid out in columns

row.description: Components are laid out in rows

labelEdge.description: Specifies how the label is created and aligned with its form control. See the Help documentation for more information.

inside.description: oj-form-layout will not create any label. Label will be created by the form control if the form control has its label-edge set to "inside". Please see the specific form control's label-edge attribute documentation for details.

start.description: oj-form-layout will create a label that's before the start of the form control if the form control has its label-edge set to "provided". If the form control specifies "inside" or "none" as its label-edge, no label will be created by oj-form-layout.

top.description: oj-form-layout will create a label that's on top of the form control if the form control has its label-edge set to "provided". If the form control specifies "inside" or "none" as its label-edge, no label will be created by oj-form-layout.

labelWidth.description: Specifies the label width. See the Help documentation for more information.

labelWrapping.description: Specifies if the label text should wrap or truncate.

maxColumns.description: Specifies the maximum number of columns. See the Help documentation for more information.

readonly.description: Specifies whether the form is readonly. See the Help documentation for more information.

userAssistanceDensity.description: Specifies the density of the form component's user assistance presentation.

compact.description: messages, help, hints, and required will not be shown inline; they will show in a mode that keeps the screen more compact, like a popup for the messages, and a required icon to indicate Required.

efficient.description: messages, help, hints, and required are all shown inline under the field with reserved space underneath.

reflow.description: If reflow, messages, help, hints, and required are all shown inline under the field with no reserved space.

style.description: The CSS style object defining the style of the label.

text.description: The text for the label. If specified, text will overwrite the numeric value that is displayed by default. The converter, scaling, and textType attributes are ignored when text is specified.

textType.description: Defines whether the label is a number or a percentage of the total value.

min.description: The minimum value of the gauge.

rotation.description: The rotation angle for the gauge. Useful for changing the direction of triangle or arrow gauges.

size.description: Fraction of area to use. Values range from 0 to 1.

svgClassName.description: The CSS style class to apply to the gauge. See the Help documentation for more information.

svgStyle.description: The inline style to apply to the gauge. See the Help documentation for more information.

thresholds.description: An array of objects specifying the gauge thresholds.

borderColor.description: The border color of the threshold.

color.description: The color of the threshold.

max.description: The upper bound of the threshold. This value is ignored for the final threshold, which uses the maximum value of the gauge.

shortDesc.description: Specific description for the threshold and overwrites the shortDesc specified on gauge. This is used for accessibility and also for customizing the tooltip text.

tooltip.description: An object containing an optional callback function for tooltip customization.

renderer.description: A function that returns a custom tooltip for a gauge. The function takes a context argument, provided by the gauge. See the Help documentation for more information.

trackResize.description: Defines whether the element will automatically render in response to changes in size. See the Help documentation for more information.

oj-legend-item.description: The oj-legend-item element is used to declare properties for legend items. See the Help documentation for more information.

borderColor.description: The border color of the marker. Only applies if symbolType is "marker" or "lineWithMarker".

categories.description: An array of categories for the legend item. Legend items currently only support a single category.

categoryVisibility.description: Defines whether the legend item corresponds to visible data items. A hollow symbol is shown if the value is "hidden".

color.description: The color of the legend symbol (line or marker). When symbolType is "lineWithMarker", this attribute defines the line color and the markerColor attribute defines the marker color.

drilling.description: Specifies whether drilling is enabled on the legend item. See the Help documentation for more information.

lineStyle.description: The line style. Only applies when the symbolType is "line" or "lineWithMarker".

lineWidth.description: The line width in pixels. Only applies when the symbolType is "line" or "lineWithMarker".

markerColor.description: The color of the marker, if different than the line color. Only applies if the symbolType is "lineWithMarker".

markerShape.description: The shape of the marker. Only applies if symbolType is "marker" or "lineWithMarker". See the Help documentation for more information.

markerSvgClassName.description: The CSS style class to apply to the marker. The style class and inline style will override any other styling specified through the options. See the Help documentation for more information.

markerSvgStyle.description: The inline style to apply to the marker. The style class and inline style will override any other styling specified through the options. See the Help documentation for more information.

pattern.description: The pattern used to fill the marker. Only applies if symbolType is "marker" or "lineWithMarker".

shortDesc.description: The description of this legend item. This is used for accessibility and for customizing the tooltip text.

source.description: The URI of the image of the legend symbol.

svgClassName.description: The CSS style class to apply to the legend item. The style class and inline style will override any other styling specified through the options. See the Help documentation for more information.

svgStyle.description: The inline style to apply to the legend item. The style class and inline style will override any other styling specified through the options. See the Help documentation for more information.

symbolType.description: The type of legend symbol to display.

oj-legend-section.description: The oj-legend-section element is used to declare properties for legend sections. See the Help documentation for more information.

collapsible.description: Whether the section is collapsible. Only applies if the legend orientation is vertical.

text.description: The title of the legend section.

textHalign.description: The horizontal alignment of the section title. If the section is collapsible or nested, only start alignment is supported.

textStyle.description: The CSS style object defining the style of the section title. The following style properties are supported: color, cursor, fontFamily, fontSize, fontStyle, fontWeight, textDecoration.

oj-legend.name: oj-legend
oj-legend.description: A legend displays an interactive description of symbols, colors, etc., used in graphical information representations.

status.description: Set the alias directly on the template element using the data-oj-as attribute instead.

as.description: An alias for the '$current' context variable passed to slot content for the nodeTemplate slot.

data.description: Specifies the DataProvider for the sections and items of the legend. See the Help documentation for more information.

drilling.description: Specifies whether drilling is enabled. Drillable objects will show a pointer cursor on hover and fire an ojDrill event on click. See the Help documentation for more information.

expanded.description: Specifies the key set containing the ids of sections that should be expanded on initial render. See the Help documentation for more information.

halign.description: Defines the horizontal alignment of the legend contents.

hiddenCategories.description: An array of categories that will be hidden.

hideAndShowBehavior.description: Defines whether the legend can be used to initiate hide and show behavior on referenced data items.

highlightedCategories.description: An array of categories that will be highlighted.

hoverBehavior.description: Defines the behavior applied when hovering over a legend item.

hoverBehaviorDelay.description: Specifies initial hover delay in milliseconds for highlighting items in legend.

orientation.description: Defines the orientation of the legend, which determines the direction in which the legend items are laid out.

scrolling.description: Defines whether scrolling is enabled for the legend.

sections.description: An array of objects specifying the legend sections.

collapsible.description: Whether the section is collapsible. Only applies if the legend orientation is vertical.

expanded.description: Whether the section is initially expanded. Only applies if the section is collapsible.

id.description: The id of the legend section. For the DataProvider case, the key for the node will be used as the id.

items.description: An array of objects with the following properties defining the legend items. Also accepts a Promise for deferred data rendering. No data will be rendered if the Promise is rejected.

borderColor.description: The border color of the marker. Only applies if symbolType is "marker" or "lineWithMarker".

categories.description: An array of categories for the legend item. Legend items currently only support a single category. If no category is specified, this defaults to the id or text of the legend item.

categoryVisibility.description: Defines whether the legend item corresponds to visible data items. A hollow symbol is shown if the value is "hidden".

color.description: The color of the legend symbol (line or marker). When symbolType is "lineWithMarker", this attribute defines the line color and the markerColor attribute defines the marker color.

drilling.description: Whether drilling is enabled on the legend item. Drillable objects will show a pointer cursor on hover and fire ojDrill event on click. To enable drilling for all legend items at once, use the drilling attribute in the top level.

id.description: The id of the legend item, which is provided as part of the context for events fired by the legend. If not specified, the id defaults to the text of the legend item if a DataProvider is not being used. For the DataProvider case, the key for the node will be used as the id.

lineStyle.description: The line style. Only applies when the symbolType is "line" or "lineWithMarker".

lineWidth.description: The line width in pixels. Only applies when the symbolType is "line" or "lineWithMarker".

markerColor.description: The color of the marker, if different than the line color. Only applies if the symbolType is "lineWithMarker".

markerShape.description: The shape of the marker. Only applies if symbolType is "marker" or "lineWithMarker". Can take the name of a built-in shape or the SVG path commands for a custom shape. Does not apply if a custom image is specified.

markerSvgClassName.description: The CSS style class to apply to the marker. The style class and inline style will override any other styling specified through the options. For tooltips and hover interactivity, it's recommended to also pass a representative color to the markerColor attribute.

markerSvgStyle.description: The inline style to apply to the marker. The style class and inline style will override any other styling specified through the options. For tooltips and hover interactivity, it's recommended to also pass a representative color to the markerColor attribute. Only SVG CSS style properties are supported.

pattern.description: The pattern used to fill the marker. Only applies if symbolType is "marker" or "lineWithMarker".

shortDesc.description: The description of this legend item. This is used for accessibility and for customizing the tooltip text.

source.description: The URI of the image of the legend symbol.

svgClassName.description: The CSS style class to apply to the legend item. The style class and inline style will override any other styling specified through the options. For tooltips and hover interactivity, it's recommended to also pass a representative color to the color attribute.

svgStyle.description: The inline style to apply to the legend item. The style class and inline style will override any other styling specified through the options. For tooltips and hover interactivity, it's recommended to also pass a representative color to the color attribute. Only SVG CSS style properties are supported.

symbolType.description: The type of legend symbol to display.

sections.description: An array of nested legend sections.

title.description: The title of the legend section.

titleHalign.description: The horizontal alignment of the section title. If the section is collapsible or nested, only start alignment is supported.

titleStyle.description: The CSS style object defining the style of the section title. The following style properties are supported: color, cursor, fontFamily, fontSize, fontStyle, fontWeight, textDecoration.

metadata.description: The metadata for adding extra trailing information. Examples of metadata are author, date etc.

oj-list-view.name: oj-list-view

styleClasses.description: Use on any element inside an item where you do not want ListView to process the click event.
Allows per-instance control of the focus highlight policy (not typically required). See the Help documentation for more information.
Use when ListView occupies the entire width of the page. Removes left and right borders in card-layout mode and adjust positioning of cards to improve visual experience.
Shows items as cards and lay them out in a grid.
Use to show a drag handle in the item to facilitate item reordering or drag and drop.
Use to show a drill-to-detail icon in the item.
Use when the page author overrides the default styling on the item root element and wants to apply the item style on some other element.

oj-list-view.description: A list view displays data items as a list or a grid with highly interactive features.

status.description: Set the alias directly on the template element using the data-oj-as attribute instead.

as.description: Specifies the alias for the current item when referenced inside the item template.

currentItem.description: Specifies the key of the item that should have keyboard focus. See the Help documentation for more information.

data.description: Specifies the data for the list. See the Help documentation for more information.

display.description: Specifies how the items should be displayed.

dnd.description: Customizes the drag and drop functionality. See the Help documentation for more information.

items.description: An object that describes drag functionality for a selected set of items. See the Help documentation for more information.

dataTypes.description: Specifies one or more MIME types to use for the dragged data in the dataTransfer object. See the Help documentation for more information.

drag.description: An optional callback function that receives the "drag" event as its argument.

dragEnd.description: An optional callback function that receives the "dragend" event as its argument.

dragStart.description: A callback function that receives the "dragstart" event and context information as its arguments.

items.description: An object that describes drop functionality for a selected set of items.

dataTypes.description: Specifies one or more data types that this component can accept. See the Help documentation for more information.

dragEnter.description: An optional callback function that receives the "dragenter" event and context information as its arguments.

dragLeave.description: An optional callback function that receives the "dragleave" event and context information as its arguments.

dragOver.description: An optional callback function that receives the "dragover" event and context information as its arguments.

drop.description: An optional callback function that receives the "drop" event and context information as its arguments.

items.description: Specify the item reordering functionality. See the Help documentation for more information.

disabled.description: Item reordering is disabled.

drillMode.description: Specifies whether expand or collapse operations are allowed.

collapsible.description: Group item can be expanded or collapsed by user.

none.description: The expand state of a group item cannot be changed by user.

expanded.description: Specifies the key set containing the keys of the items that should be expanded. See the Help documentation for more information.

firstSelectedItem.description: Specifies the key and data of the first selected item. See the Help documentation for more information.

gridlines.description: Customizes the functionality of how gridlines are shown in various parts of the list.

item.description: Specifies whether the grid lines should be visible.

visibleExceptLast.description: The horizontal gridlines are visible, except for the last item. Note this will not have an effect for themes that renders a bottom border for the component.

groupHeaderPosition.description: Specifies whether group header should stick to the top as user scrolls.

static.description: The group header position updates as user scrolls.

sticky.description: The group header is fixed at the top when user scrolls.

item.description: Customizes the functionality of each item on the list.

focusable.description: Specifies whether the item can receive keyboard focus. See the Help documentation for more information.

renderer.description: Specifies the renderer for the item. See the Help documentation for more information.

selectable.description: Specifies whether the item can be selected. See the Help documentation for more information.

scrollPolicy.description: Specifies how data are fetched as user scrolls down the list.

auto.description: The behavior is determined by the component. By default the behavior is the same as "loadMoreOnScroll" except when legacy TableDataSource is used, in which case the behavior is the same as "loadAll".

loadMoreOnScroll.description: Additional data is fetched when the user scrolls towards the bottom of the ListView.

scrollPolicyOptions.description: Specifies fetch options for scrolling behaviors that trigger data fetches. See the Help documentation for more information.

fetchSize.description: The number of items to fetch in each block

maxCount.description: The maximum total number of items to fetch

scroller.description: The element used to determine the scroll position as well as the maximum scroll position. See the Help documentation for more information.

scrollPosition.description: Specifies the current scroll position of the list. See the Help documentation for more information.

x.description: the horizontal position in pixels

y.description: the vertical position in pixels

index.description: the zero-based index of the item. If scrollPolicy is set to 'loadMoreOnScroll' and the index is greater than maxCount set in scrollPolicyOptions, then it will scroll and fetch until the end of the list is reached and there's no more items to fetch.

parent.description: the key of the parent where the index is relative to. If not specified, then the root is assumed

key.description: the key of the item. If DataProvider is used for data and the key does not exists in the DataProvider, then the value is ignored. If DataProvider is not used then ListView will fetch and scroll until the item is found or the end of the list is reached and there's no more items to fetch.

offsetX.description: the horizontal offset in pixels relative to the item identified by key/index.

offsetY.description: the vertical offset in pixels relative to the item identified by key/index.

selected.description: Specifies the keys of the current selected items. See the Help documentation for more information.

status.description: Use selected attribute instead.

selection.description: Specifies the current selections in the list. See the Help documentation for more information.

multiple.description: Multiple items can be selected at the same time.

none.description: Selection is disabled.

single.description: Only a single item can be selected at a time.

selectionRequired.description: Specifies whether selection is required on the ListView.

translations.description: A collection of translated resources from the translation bundle, or null if this component has no resources.

accessibleNavigateSkipItems.description: Provides properties to customize the screen reader text when focus skips a number of items as a result of up/down arrow navigation in card layout mode.

accessibleReorderAfterItem.description: Provides properties to customize the screen reader text when the tentative drop target is after a certain item.

accessibleReorderBeforeItem.description: Provides properties to customize the screen reader text when the tentative drop target is before a certain item.

accessibleReorderInsideItem.description: Provides properties to customize the screen reader text when the tentative drop target is inside a certain item.

accessibleReorderTouchInstructionText.description: Provides properties to customize the screen reader touch instructional text for reordering items.

msgItemsAppended.description: Provides properties to customize the message text used by ListView when items are appended.

msgNoData.description: Provides properties to customize the message text used by ListView when there are no items.

oj-n-box.name: oj-n-box
oj-n-box.description: NBox is an interactive data visualization (typically found in Human Capital Management applications) in which employees are grouped and compared across two dimensions.  Each dimension can be split into multiple ranges.

animationOnDataChange.description: Specifies the animation that is applied on data changes.

animationOnDisplay.description: Specifies the animation that is shown on initial display.

status.description: Set the alias directly on the template element using the data-oj-as attribute instead.

as.description: Specifies the alias for the current item when referenced inside the nodeTemplate.

cellContent.description: Specifies the content displayed in cells. See the Help documentation for more information.

cellMaximize.description: Specifies whether cell maximize/de-maximize gestures are enabled.

cells.description: Specifies the list of cells. Also accepts a Promise for deferred data rendering.

label.description: The text for the cell label.

column.description: The id of the column containing this cell.

labelHalign.description: The horizontal alignment value for the cell label.

labelStyle.description: The CSS style object defining the style of the cell label. The following style properties are supported: color, cursor, fontFamily, fontSize, fontStyle, fontWeight, textDecoration. The default value comes from the CSS and varies based on theme.

svgClassName.description: The CSS style class for this cell. Used for customizing the cell background and border.

svgStyle.description: The CSS style object for this cell. Used for customizing the cell background and border. Only SVG CSS style properties are supported. The default value comes from the CSS and varies based on theme.

maximizedSvgStyle.description: The CSS style object for this cell. Used for customizing the maximized cell background and border. Only SVG CSS style properties are supported. The default value comes from the CSS and varies based on theme.

maximizedSvgClassName.description: The CSS style class for this cell. Used for customizing the minimized cell background and border.

minimizedSvgStyle.description: The CSS style object for this cell. Used for customizing the minimized cell background and border. Only SVG CSS style properties are supported. The default value comes from the CSS and varies based on theme.

minimizedSvgClassName.description: The CSS style class for this cell. Used for customizing the minimized cell background and border.

row.description: The id of the row containing this cell.

showCount.description: Determines when to display the cell count label (extra info displayed after primary cell label). "off" never show the count label. "on" always show the count label. Show countLabel value if specified, otherwise use a simple node count. "auto" show the count label if countLabel attribute is defined.

shortDesc.description: The description of this cell. This is used for accessibility.

columns.description: Specifies the list of columns. Also accepts a Promise for deferred data rendering.

id.description: The id of the column. Used to identify this column.

label.description: The text for the column label.

labelStyle.description: The CSS style object defining the style of the column label. The following style properties are supported: color, cursor, fontFamily, fontSize, fontStyle, fontWeight, textDecoration.

columnsTitle.description: The text for the title on the column edge.

countLabel.description: A function that returns custom text for the cell count labels.

data.description: Specifies the data provider for the NBox. See the Help documentation for more information.

groupAttributes.description: An array of attributes for styling the group nodes.

groupBehavior.description: Specifies how nodes should be grouped.

hiddenCategories.description: An array of category strings used for filtering. Data items with any category matching an item in this array will be filtered.

highlightMatch.description: The matching condition for the highlightedCategories property. See the Help documentation for more information.

highlightedCategories.description: An array of category strings used for highlighting. Data items matching categories in this array will be highlighted.

hoverBehavior.description: Defines the behavior applied when hovering over data items.

labelTruncation.description: Specifies node label truncation behavior. See the Help documentation for more information.

maximizedColumn.description: The id of the column to be maximized.

maximizedRow.description: The id of the row to be maximized.

nodes.description: The list of nodes. Also accepts a Promise for deferred data rendering.

id.description: The node id. The node id should be set by the application if the DataProvider is not being used.

borderColor.description: The border color of the node. Does not apply if custom image is specified.

borderWidth.description: The border width of the node in pixels. Does not apply if custom image is specified.

categories.description: An optional array of additional category strings corresponding to this data item. This enables highlighting and filtering of individual data items through interactions with other visualization elements. Defaults to node's id if unspecified.

color.description: The color of the node. Does not apply if custom image is specified.

column.description: The column id for this node.

groupCategory.description: The group category this node belongs to. Nodes with the same groupCategory will be grouped together.

icon.description: Defines the primary icon for this node.

borderColor.description: The border color of this icon.

borderRadius.description: The border radius of this icon. CSS border-radius values accepted. Note that non-% values (including unitless) get interpreted as 'px'.

borderWidth.description: The border width of this icon.

color.description: The fill color of this icon.

height.description: The height of this icon.

pattern.description: The pattern of this icon.

shape.description: The shape of this icon. Can take the name of a built-in shape or the SVG path commands for a custom shape.

source.description: The URL of an image to display for this icon.

initials.description: The initials displayed for this icon.

svgClassName.description: The CSS style class defining the style of this icon. Will not be applied if initials are specified.

svgStyle.description: The CSS style object defining the style of this icon. Only SVG CSS style properties are supported. Will not be applied if initials are specified. The default value comes from the CSS and varies based on theme.

width.description: The width of this icon.

indicatorColor.description: The background color for the indicator section of this node.

indicatorIcon.description: Defines the indicator icon for this node.

borderColor.description: The border color of this indicator icon.

borderRadius.description: The border radius of this indicator icon. CSS border-radius values accepted. Note that non-% values (including unitless) get interpreted as 'px'.

borderWidth.description: The border width of this indicator icon.

color.description: The fill color of this indicator icon.

height.description: The height of this indicator icon.

opacity.description: The opacity of this indicator icon.

pattern.description: The pattern of this indicator icon.

shape.description: The shape of this indicator icon. Can take the name of a built-in shape or the SVG path commands for a custom shape.

source.description: The URL of an image to display for this indicator icon.

svgClassName.description: The CSS style class defining the style of this indicator icon.

svgStyle.description: The CSS style object defining the style of this indicator icon. Only SVG CSS style properties are supported. The default value comes from the CSS and varies based on theme.

width.description: The width of this indicator icon.

row.description: The row id for this node.

label.description: The text for the node label.

secondaryLabel.description: The text for the secondary node label.

svgClassName.description: The CSS style class defining the style of this node.

svgStyle.description: The CSS style object defining the style of this node. Only SVG CSS style properties are supported. The default value comes from the CSS and varies based on theme.

xPercentage.description: An optional horizontal position (as a percentage) to be used in the average position calculation when grouping across cells.

yPercentage.description: An optional vertical position (as a percentage) to be used in the average position calculation when grouping across cells.

shortDesc.description: The description of this node. This is used for accessibility and also for customizing the tooltip text.

otherColor.description: The color for the "other" group nodes. See the Help documentation for more information.

otherThreshold.description: The threshold for aggregating nodes into an "other" group node. See the Help documentation for more information.

rows.description: The list of rows. Also accepts a Promise for deferred data rendering.

id.description: The id of the row. Used to identify this row.

label.description: The text for the row label.

labelStyle.description: The CSS style object defining the style of the row label. The following style properties are supported: color, cursor, fontFamily, fontSize, fontStyle, fontWeight, textDecoration.

rowsTitle.description: The text for the title on the row edge.

selection.description: Specifies the ids of the selected nodes.

selectionMode.description: Specifies the selection behavior on the NBox. See the Help documentation for more information.

multiple.description: Multiple items can be selected at the same time.

none.description: Selection is disabled.

single.description: Only a single item can be selected at a time.

styleDefaults.description: An object defining the style defaults for this NBox.

animationDuration.description: The duration of the animations in milliseconds.

cellDefaults.description: An object defining the style defaults for cells.

labelHalign.description: The horizontal alignment value for the cell label.

labelStyle.description: The CSS style object defining the style of the cell labels.

maximizedSvgStyle.description: The CSS style object defining the styles of the cell background and border when the cell is maximized.

minimizedSvgStyle.description: The CSS style object defining the styles of the cell background and border when the cell is minimized.

showCount.description: Specifies when to display the cell count label. See the Help documentation for more information.

svgStyle.description: The CSS style object defining the styles of the cell background and border.

columnLabelStyle.description: The CSS style object defining the style of the column labels.

columnsTitleStyle.description: The CSS style object defining the style of the columns title.

hoverBehaviorDelay.description: Specifies initial hover delay in milliseconds for highlighting data items.

nodeDefaults.description: An object defining the style defaults for nodes.

borderColor.description: The default color of the node borders. The default value varies based on theme.

borderWidth.description: The default width of the node borders. The default value varies based on theme.

color.description: The default background color of the nodes.

iconDefaults.description: An object defining the style defaults for the node icons.

background.description: The URL of an image to display by default for the node icons.

borderColor.description: The default border color of the node icons. The default value varies based on theme.

borderRadius.description: The default border radius of the node icons. See the Help documentation for more information.

borderWidth.description: The default border width of the node icons. The default value varies based on theme.

color.description: The default fill color of the node icons.

opacity.description: The default opacity of the node icons.

pattern.description: The default fill pattern of the node icons.

width.description: The default width of the node icons. If the value is 0, the width will be automatically based on the remaining node contents.

indicatorColor.description: The default background color of the node indicator sections.

indicatorIconDefaults.description: An object defining the style defaults for the node indicator icons.

rowsTitleStyle.description: The CSS style object defining the style of the rows title.

tooltip.description: An object containing an optional callback function for tooltip customization.

renderer.description: A function that returns a custom tooltip. See the Help documentation for more information.

touchResponse.description: Specifies configuration options for touch and hold delays on mobile devices. See the Help documentation for more information.

trackResize.description: Defines whether the element will automatically render in response to changes in size. See the Help documentation for more information.

translations.description: A collection of translated resources from the translation bundle, or null if this component has no resources.

componentName.description: Used to describe the data visualization type for accessibility.

highlightedCount.description: Used to indicate number of highlighted nodes in a cell.

labelAndValue.description: Used to display a label and its value.

labelCountWithTotal.description: Used to display a count out of a total.

oj-navigation-list.name: oj-navigation-list

styleClasses.description: Use this class to condense horizontal navigation list items depending on screen size.
Any list item can be disabled by adding the oj-disabled class to that element
Allows per-instance control of the focus highlight policy (not typically required). See the Help documentation for more information.
Use this class to add a horizontal divider line between two categories of items.
Use this class to render a divider between list items. Note: On IE11, this is not supported when overflow attribute is set to 'popup'.
Use this class to add an icon to a list item.
Use this class to wrap item label text. Note: On IE11, this is not supported when overflow attribute is set to 'popup'.
When arbitrary content is placed inside an item's content area, its title text can be marked using this style class. This helps the component in identifying the Item's label.
Use this class to prevent automatic navigation to a URL within a list item. See the Help documentation for more information.
Use this class to display a horizontal Navigation List with icons and labels stacked. Applicable only when edge is top.

styleClasses.description: Use this class to display a horizontal Navigation List with icons and labels stacked. Applicable only when edge is top.

oj-picto-chart-item.name: oj-picto-chart-item
oj-picto-chart-item.description: The oj-picto-chart-item element is used to declare properties for picto chart items. See the Help documentation for more information.

borderColor.description: The border color of the item. Does not apply if custom image is specified.

borderWidth.description: The border width of the item in pixels. Does not apply if custom image is specified.

categories.description: An array of category strings corresponding to this picto chart item. This allows highlighting and filtering of items.

color.description: The color of the item. Does not apply if custom image is specified.

columnSpan.description: The number of columns each shape (or custom image) spans. Used for creating a picto chart with mixed item sizes.

count.description: Specifies the number of times that the shape (or custom image) is drawn. See the Help documentation for more information.

drilling.description: Whether drilling is enabled on the item. Drillable items will show a pointer cursor on hover and fire an ojDrill event on click (double click if selection is enabled). See the Help documentation for more information.

name.description: The name of the item. Used for default tooltip and accessibility.

rowSpan.description: The number of rows each shape (or custom image) spans. Used for creating a picto chart with mixed item sizes.

shape.description: The shape of the item. In addition to the built-in shapes, it may also take SVG path commands to specify a custom shape. See the Help documentation for more information.

shortDesc.description: The description of the item. This is used for customizing the tooltip text.

source.description: The URI of the custom image. If specified, it takes precedence over shape.

sourceHover.description: The optional URI for the hover state. If not specified, the source image will be used.

sourceHoverSelected.description: The optional URI for the hover selected state. If not specified, the source image will be used.

sourceSelected.description: The optional URI for the selected state. If not specified, the source image will be used.

svgClassName.description: The CSS style class to apply to the item. See the Help documentation for more information.

svgStyle.description: The inline style to apply to the item. See the Help documentation for more information.

oj-picto-chart.name: oj-picto-chart
oj-picto-chart.description: A picto chart displays information using icons to visualize an absolute number or the relative sizes of the different parts of a population.

animationDuration.description: The duration of the animations in milliseconds.

animationOnDataChange.description: Specifies the animation that is applied on data changes.

animationOnDisplay.description: Specifies the animation shown on initial display.

status.description: Set the alias directly on the template element using the data-oj-as attribute instead.

as.description: An alias for the '$current' context variable passed to slot content for the itemTemplate slot.

columnCount.description: The number of columns in the picto chart. If unspecified, the number of columns will be automatically computed.

columnWidth.description: The width of a column in pixels. If unspecified, the column width will be automatically computed. See the Help documentation for more information.

data.description: Specifies the DataProvider for the picto chart. See the Help documentation for more information.

drilling.description: Specifies whether drilling is enabled. Drillable objects will show a pointer cursor on hover and fire an ojDrill event on click (double click if selection is enabled). See the Help documentation for more information.

hiddenCategories.description: An array of category strings used for filtering. Data items with any category matching an item in this array will be filtered.

highlightMatch.description: The matching condition for the highlightedCategories property. See the Help documentation for more information.

highlightedCategories.description: An array of category strings used for highlighting. Data items matching categories in this array will be highlighted.

hoverBehavior.description: Defines the behavior applied when hovering over data items.

hoverBehaviorDelay.description: Specifies initial hover delay in milliseconds for highlighting data items.

items.description: An array of objects that define the picto chart items. See the Help documentation for more information.

id.description: The item id. The item id should be set by the application if the DataProvider is not being used.

name.description: The name of the item. Used for default tooltip and accessibility.

shape.description: The shape of the item. Can take the name of a built-in shape or the SVG path commands for a custom shape. "None" will make the item transparent and can be used to create gaps. Does not apply if custom image is specified.

color.description: The color of the item. Does not apply if custom image is specified.

borderColor.description: The border color of the item. Does not apply if custom image is specified.

borderWidth.description: The border width of the item in pixels. Does not apply if custom image is specified.

source.description: The URI of the custom image. If specified, it takes precedence over shape.

svgClassName.description: The CSS style class to apply to the item. The style class and inline style will override any other styling specified with other properties. For tooltip interactivity, it's recommended to also pass a representative color to the item color attribute. Does not apply if custom image is specified.

svgStyle.description: The inline style to apply to the item. The style class and inline style will override any other styling specified with other properties. For tooltip interactivity, it's recommended to also pass a representative color to the item color attribute. Does not apply if custom image is specified. Only SVG CSS style properties are supported.

sourceHover.description: The optional URI for the hover state. If not specified, the source image will be used.

sourceSelected.description: The optional URI for the selected state. If not specified, the source image will be used.

sourceHoverSelected.description: The optional URI for the hover selected state. If not specified, the source image will be used.

count.description: Specifies the number of times that the shape (or custom image) is drawn. Fractional counts (such as 4.5) are supported; however, fractions other than the multiples of 0.5 should be avoided because the fractional rendering ignores the gaps between shapes and the irregularity of the shapes.

rowSpan.description: The number of rows each shape (or custom image) spans. Used for creating a pictoChart with mixed item sizes.

columnSpan.description: The number of columns each shape (or custom image) spans. Used for creating a pictoChart with mixed item sizes.

shortDesc.description: Short description string for accessibility users.

categories.description: An array of category strings corresponding to this item. If not specified, defaults to the item id or name. This enables highlighting and filtering of individual data items through interactions with other visualization elements.

drilling.description: Whether drilling is enabled for the item. Drillable items will show a pointer cursor on hover and fire an ojDrill event on click (double click if selection is enabled). To enable drilling for all items at once, use the drilling attribute in the top level.

layout.description: Specifies the direction in which items are laid out.

layoutOrigin.description: Specifies where the first item is rendered. Subsequent items follow the first item according to the layout.

rowCount.description: The number of rows in the picto chart. If unspecified, the number of rows will be automatically computed.

rowHeight.description: The height of a row in pixels. If unspecified, the row height will be automatically computed. See the Help documentation for more information.

selection.description: An array of id strings, used to define the selected objects.

multiple.description: Multiple items can be selected at the same time.

none.description: Selection is disabled.

single.description: Only a single item can be selected at a time.

tooltip.description: An object containing an optional callback function for tooltip customization.

renderer.description: A function that returns a custom tooltip. The function takes a context argument, provided by the picto chart. See the Help documentation for more information.

trackResize.description: Defines whether the element will automatically render in response to changes in size. See the Help documentation for more information.

translations.description: A collection of translated resources from the translation bundle, or null if this component has no resources.

componentName.description: Used to describe the data visualization type for accessibility.

labelAndValue.description: Used to display a label and its value.

labelClearSelection.description: Text shown for clearing multiple selection on touch devices.

labelCountWithTotal.description: Used to display a count out of a total.

labelDataVisualization.description: Label for data visualizations used for accessibility.

labelInvalidData.description: Text shown when the component receives invalid data.

labelNoData.description: Text shown when the component receives no data.

stateCollapsed.description: Used to describe the collapsed state for accessibility.

stateDrillable.description: Used to describe a drillable object for accessibility.

stateExpanded.description: Used to describe the expanded state for accessibility.

stateHidden.description: Used to describe the hidden state for accessibility.

stateIsolated.description: Used to describe the isolated state for accessibility.

stateMaximized.description: Used to describe the maximized state for accessibility.

stateMinimized.description: Used to describe the minimized state for accessibility.

stateSelected.description: Used to describe the selected state for accessibility.

stateUnselected.description: Used to describe the unselected state for accessibility.

stateVisible.description: Used to describe the visible state for accessibility.
