styleClasses.description: Allows per-instance control of the focus highlight policy (not typically required). See the Help documentation for more information.

styleClasses.name: oj-focus-highlight
styleClasses.description: Allows per-instance control of the focus highlight policy (not typically required). See the Help documentation for more information.

oj-popup.description: A popup temporarily 'pops up' content in the foreground.

focusLoss.description: defines auto dismissal behavior when focus leaves the content of the popup or associated launcher. In addition, if what the popup is positioned to is not visible within an overflow area, the popup will auto close dismiss.

none.description: disables auto dismissal behaviors.

chrome.description: Specifies whether to use the border, shadow, and background colors from the active theme.

default.description: describes the popups border, shadow, and background color defined by the active theme.

none.description: turns off the outer chrome defined by the active theme.

initialFocus.description: Specifies whether the popup steals focus to its content when initially opened.

auto.description: is derived from the values of the modality and autoDismiss properties

firstFocusable.description: defines that a popup should grab focus to the first focusable element within the popup's content.

none.description: prevents the popup from stealing focus when open.

popup.description: focus to the root popup container (good choice for touch platforms).

modality.description: Specifies whether the popup should block user input to the page.

modal.description: The popup is modal. Interactions with other page elements are disabled. Modal popups overlay other page elements.

position.description: Specifies the position of a popup when launched. See the Help documentation for more information.

at.description: Defines which position on the target element ("of") to align the positioned element against.

horizontal.description: Defines the horizontal alignment of what the popup is aligned to.

end.description: evaluates to "right" in LTR mode and "left" in RTL mode.

start.description: evaluates to "left" in LTR mode and "right" in RTL mode.

vertical.description: Defines the vertical alignment of what the popup is aligned to.

fit.description: shift the element away from the edge of the window.

flip.description: the element to the opposite side of the target and the collision detection is run again to see if it will fit. Whichever side allows more of the element to be visible will be used.

flipcenter.description: first applies the flip rule and follow with center alignment.

flipfit.description: first applies the flip logic, placing the element on whichever side allows more of the element to be visible. Then the fit logic is applied to ensure as much of the element is visible as possible.

none.description: no collision detection.

my.description: Defines which edge on the popup to align with the target ("of") element.

horizontal.description: Defines the horizontal alignment of the popup.

end.description: evaluates to "right" in LTR mode and "left" in RTL mode.

start.description: evaluates to "left" in LTR mode and "right" in RTL mode.

vertical.description: Defines the vertical alignment of the popup.

of.description: Which element to position the popup against. See the Help documentation for more information.

offset.description: Defines a point offset in pixels from the ("my") alignment.

x.description: Horizontal alignment offset.

y.description: Vertical alignment offset.

tail.description: Specifies whether to display a decoration pointing from the popup to the launching element. See the Help documentation for more information.

none.description: no decoration will be displayed from the popup pointing to the launcher.

simple.description: enables showing the tail defined by the current theme.

translations.description: A collection of translated resources from the translation bundle, or null if this component has no resources.

ariaCloseSkipLink.description: Label assigned to a hidden anchor tag used for accessibility navigation on platforms supporting VoiceOver. The link is injected as a sibling to the context area of an open popup and used for ojPopup#close activation.

ariaFocusSkipLink.description: Label assigned to a hidden anchor tag used for accessibility navigation on platforms supporting VoiceOver. The link is injected as a sibling to the launcher of an open popup. The launcher is passed as the first argument to ojPopup#open. Activation of the link will move focus to the content of the associated popup.

ariaLiveRegionInitialFocusFirstFocusable.description: Message announced to a WAI-ARIA live region on desktop platforms when a popup opens and steals initial focus.
Message announced to a WAI-ARIA live region on platforms supporting VoiceOver when a popup opens and steals initial focus.

ariaLiveRegionInitialFocusNone.description: Message announced to a WAI-ARIA live region on desktop platforms when a popup opens but doesn't change focus.

ariaLiveRegionInitialFocusNoneTouch.description: Message announced to a WAI-ARIA live region on platforms supporting VoiceOver when a popup opens but doesn't change focus.

disabled.description: Specifies if the component is disabled. If true, then all of its inputs and labels are also disabled. See the Help documentation for more information.

readonly.description: Specifies whether the component is read-only. A read-only element cannot be modified, but user interaction is allowed. See the Help documentation for more information.

compact.description: Messages, help, hints, and required will not be shown inline; they will show in a mode that keeps the screen more compact, like a popup for the messages, and a required icon to indicate Required.

efficient.description: Messages, help, hints, and required are all shown inline under the field with reserved space.

reflow.description: Messages, help, hints, and required are all shown inline under the field with no reserved space.

valid.description: The validity state of the component

invalidHidden.description: The component has invalid messages hidden and no invalid messages showing. An invalid message is one with severity "error" or higher.

invalidShown.description: The component has invalid messages showing. An invalid message is one with severity "error" or higher.

pending.description: The component is waiting for the validation state to be determined. The "pending" state is set at the start of the convert/validate process.

reset.description: Resets the component by clearing all messages and messages attributes, and updates the component's display value using the attribute value.

showMessages.description: Takes all deferred messages and shows them.

oj-status-meter-gauge.description: A status meter gauge displays information graphically, highlighting a specific metric value's progress in relation to its thresholds.  Horizontal, vertical, and circular formats are supported.

angleExtent.description: Specifies the angle extent of a gauge with circular orientation. Value should be provided in degrees.

animationDuration.description: The duration of the animations in milliseconds.

animationOnDataChange.description: Defines the animation that is applied on data changes.

animationOnDisplay.description: Defines the animation that is shown on initial display.

borderRadius.description: Specifies the border radius of the indicator and plot area. See the Help documentation for more information.

indicatorSize.description: Defines the ratio of relative thickness of the indicator to the plot area.

label.description: An object defining the label.

position.description: Specifies the label position for horizontal and vertical gauges. See the Help documentation for more information.

style.description: The CSS style object to apply to the label. The following style properties are supported: color, cursor, fontFamily, fontSize, fontStyle, fontWeight, textDecoration.

labelledBy.description: Establishes a relationship between this component and another element, typically an oj-label custom element. See the Help documentation for more information.

rendered.description: Defines if the label is rendered. If set to auto, the label is rendered if the orientation is circular.

scaling.description: The scaling behavior of the labels. When using a converter, scaling should be set to none, as the formatted result may not be compatible with the scaling suffixes.

style.description: The CSS style object to apply to the label.

text.description: The text for the label. If specified, text will overwrite the numeric value that is displayed by default. See the Help documentation for more information.

textType.description: Defines whether the label is a number or a percentage of the total value.

min.description: The minimum value of the gauge.

orientation.description: Defines the type of status meter to be rendered.

plotArea.description: Plot Area for Status Meter Gauge

borderColor.description: The border color of the plot area.

borderRadius.description: Specifies the border radius of the plot area shape. See the Help documentation for more information.

oj-sunburst-node.description: The oj-sunburst-node element is used to declare properties for sunburst nodes. See the Help documentation for more information.

borderWidth.description: The border width of the node.

pattern.description: The pattern used to fill the node.

radius.description: The radius of the node relative to the other nodes.

selectable.description: Specifies whether the node will be selectable.

oj-sunburst.name: oj-sunburst
oj-sunburst.description: A sunburst is an interactive data visualization in which hierarchical data is represented in concentric rings.  Each ring segment is proportionally sized relative to the other segments at a given level.

animationDuration.description: Specifies the animation duration in milliseconds. For data change animations with multiple stages, the value specifies the duration of each stage.

animationOnDataChange.description: Specifies the animation that is applied on data changes.

animationOnDisplay.description: Specifies the animation that is shown on initial display.

animationUpdateColor.description: Specifies the color displayed during a data change animation when a node is updated.

status.description: Set the alias directly on the template element using the data-oj-as attribute instead.

as.description: An alias for the '$current' context variable passed to slot content for the nodeTemplate slot.

colorLabel.description: Specifies the label displayed in the legend describing the color metric of the sunburst.

data.description: Specifies the DataProvider for the sunburst. See the Help documentation for more information.

displayLevels.description: The number of levels of nodes to display. By default all nodes are displayed.

drilling.description: Specifies whether drilling is enabled. Drillable nodes will show a pointer cursor on hover and fire ojBeforeDrill and ojDrill events on click (double click if selection is enabled). See the Help documentation for more information.

expanded.description: Specifies the key set containing the ids of sunburst nodes that should be expanded on initial render. See the Help documentation for more information.

hiddenCategories.description: An array of category strings used for filtering. Nodes with any category matching an item in this array will be filtered.

highlightMatch.description: The matching condition for the highlightedCategories property. See the Help documentation for more information.

highlightedCategories.description: An array of category strings used for highlighting. Nodes matching categories in this array will be highlighted.

hoverBehavior.description: Defines the behavior applied when hovering over the nodes.

hoverBehaviorDelay.description: Specifies initial hover delay in milliseconds for highlighting nodes.

nodeDefaults.description: An object defining default properties for the nodes. See the Help documentation for more information.

borderColor.description: The default border color of the nodes.

borderWidth.description: The default border width of the nodes.

hoverColor.description: The color of the node hover feedback.

labelDisplay.description: The label display behavior for the nodes. See the Help documentation for more information.

labelHalign.description: The horizontal alignment for labels displayed within the node. Only applies to rotated text.

labelMinLength.description: The minimum number of visible characters needed to render a truncated label. See the Help documentation for more information.

labelStyle.description: The CSS style object defining the style of the label.

selectedInnerColor.description: The inner color of the node selection feedback.

selectedOuterColor.description: The outer color of the node selection feedback.

showDisclosure.description: Specifies whether to display the expand/collapse button on hover.

nodes.description: An array of objects defining the data for the nodes. Also accepts a Promise for deferred data rendering.

borderColor.description: The border color of the node.

borderWidth.description: The border width of the node.

categories.description: An optional array of category strings corresponding to this data item. This enables highlighting and filtering of individual data items through interactions with the legend and other visualization elements. The categories array of each node is required to be a superset of the categories array of its parent node. If not specified, the ids of the node and its ancestors will be used.

color.description: The fill color of the node.

drilling.description: Specifies whether drilling is enabled for the node. Drillable nodes will show a pointer cursor on hover and fire an ojDrill event on click (double click if selection is enabled). To enable drilling for all nodes at once, use the drilling attribute in the top level.

id.description: The id of the node. For the DataProvider case, the key for the node will be used as the id.

label.description: The label for this node.

labelDisplay.description: The label display behavior for the nodes. More labels are generally displayed when using rotation, with the trade off of readability. When auto is used, rotated or horizontal labels will be used based on the client browser and platform.

labelHalign.description: The horizontal alignment for labels displayed within the node. Only applies to rotated text.

labelStyle.description: The CSS style object defining the style of the label. The following style properties are supported: color, cursor, fontFamily, fontSize, fontStyle, fontWeight, textDecoration. The default value comes from the CSS and varies based on theme. The default value comes from the CSS and varies based on theme.

nodes.description: An array of objects with properties for the child nodes.

pattern.description: The pattern used to fill the node.

radius.description: The radius of the node relative to the other nodes.

selectable.description: Specifies whether or not the node will be selectable.

shortDesc.description: The description of this node. This is used for accessibility and also for customizing the tooltip text.

showDisclosure.description: Specifies whether to display the expand/collapse button on hover for a specific node. If the button is clicked, the expanded attribute is updated with the new array of node ids.

svgClassName.description: The CSS style class to apply to the node. The style class and inline style will override any other styling specified through the properties. For tooltip interactivity, it's recommended to also pass a representative color to the node color attribute.

svgStyle.description: The inline style to apply to the node. The style class and inline style will override any other styling specified through the properties. For tooltip interactivity, it's recommended to also pass a representative color to the node color attribute. Only SVG CSS style properties are supported. The default value comes from the CSS and varies based on theme.

value.description: The value of the node, which determines the relative size of the node.

rootNode.description: The id of the root node. When specified, only the root node and children of the root will be displayed.

rootNodeContent.description: An object defining custom root node content for the sunburst.

renderer.description: A function that returns custom root node content. The function takes a context argument, provided by the sunburst. See the Help documentation for more information.

startAngle.description: Specifies the starting angle of the sunburst. Valid values are numbers between 0 and 360.

oj-swipe-actions.name: oj-swipe-actions

styleClasses.description: Designed to tag swipe action items within an oj-list-view.

Designed for use with item in oj-list-view that contains the oj-swipe-actions element, specifically this will remove the padding around the content of the item so that the swipe actions can take the full height.

styleClasses.name: oj-swipeactions-[swipe-option]
styleClasses.description: Designed to tag swipe action items within an oj-list-view.

values.name: neutral
values.description: Designed for use with an action item that shows more available actions that users can perform.

values.name: attention
values.description: Designed for use with an action item that tags the associated item in oj-list-view

values.name: danger
values.description: Designed for use with an action item that performs an explicit action like deleting the associated item in oj-list-view.

values.name: default
values.description: Designed for use with an action item that should get all the space when user swipes pass the threshold distance. This is usually the last item within the template

styleClasses.name: oj-swipeactions-container

ojBeforeRowEditEnd.description: Triggered before the table is going to exit edit mode. See the Help documentation for more information.

componentElement.description: A reference to the Table root element.

parentElement.description: Empty rendered TR element.

mode.description: The mode of the row. It can be "edit" or "navigation".

cancelEdit.description: true if the edit should be negated based on actions (i.e. escape key).

ojRowAction.description: Triggered when user performs an action gesture on a row.

originalEvent.description: The DOM event that triggers the action.

ojSort.description: Triggered when a sort is performed on the table.

header.description: The key of the header which was sorted on.

bottom.description: Named slot for the Table's bottom panel where applications can add content such as a paging control. The Table will render the content provided at the bottom of the Table element. The content specified should not include any styling that may conflict with the Table's positioning. Unsupported styling includes, but is not limited to, margins and absolute positioning.

cellTemplate.description: Named slot for the Table's default cell template. The slot content must be a <template> element. The content of the template should not include the <td> element, only what's inside it.

row.description: The data for the row contained the current cell being rendered.

index.description: The zero-based index of the current row being rendered.

columnIndex.description: The zero-based index of the current column being rendered.

key.description: The key of the current cell being rendered.

mode.description: The mode of the row containing the cell. It can be "edit" or "navigation".

contextMenu.description: The contextMenu slot is set on the oj-menu instance within this element. It designates the JET Menu to launch as a context menu.

footerTemplate.description: Named slot for the Table's default footer template. The slot content must be a <template> element. The content of the template should not include the <td> element, only what's inside it.

headerTemplate.description: Named slot for the Table's default header template. The slot content must be a <template> element. The content of the template should not include the <td> element, only what's inside it.

data.description: The data object for the current header.

noData.description: The noData slot is used to specify the content to display when the table is empty. The slot content must be a <template> element. If not specified then a default no data message will be displayed.

rowTemplate.description: Named slot for the Table's default row template. The slot content must be a <template> element. The content of the template should include the <tr> element.

data.description: The data for the current row being rendered.

index.description: The zero-based index of the current row being rendered.

key.description: The key of the current row being rendered.

mode.description: The mode of the row containing the cell. It can be "edit" or "navigation".

oj-tag-cloud-item.description: The oj-tag-cloud-item element is used to declare properties for tag cloud items. See the Help documentation for more information.

categories.description: An array of category strings corresponding to the tag cloud items. This allows highlighting and filtering of items.

oj-tag-cloud.name: oj-tag-cloud
oj-tag-cloud.description: A tag cloud is an interactive data visualization of textual data, where the importance of each tagged word or phrase is represented by font size or color.

animationOnDataChange.description: Specifies the animation that is applied on data changes.

animationOnDisplay.description: Specifies the animation that is shown on initial display.

status.description: Set the alias directly on the template element using the data-oj-as attribute instead.

as.description: An alias for the '$current' context variable passed to slot content for the itemTemplate slot.

data.description: Specifies the DataProvider for the tag cloud. See the Help documentation for more information.

hiddenCategories.description: An array of category strings used for category filtering. Data items with a category in hiddenCategories will be filtered.

highlightMatch.description: The matching condition for the highlightedCategories property. See the Help documentation for more information.

highlightedCategories.description: An array of category strings used for highlighting. Data items matching categories in this array will be highlighted.

hoverBehavior.description: Defines the behavior applied when hovering over data items.

items.description: An array of objects defining the data items for the tag cloud items. Also accepts a Promise for deferred data rendering.

categories.description: An array of category strings corresponding to the tag cloud items. This allows highlighting and filtering of items.

color.description: The color of the text. Will be overridden by any color defined in the style option. The default value comes from the CSS and varies based on theme.

id.description: The item id should be set by the application if the DataProvider is not being used. The row key will be used as id in the DataProvider case.

label.description: The text of the item.

shortDesc.description: The description of the item. This is used for customizing the tooltip text.

svgStyle.description: The CSS style object defining the style of the item text. Only SVG CSS style properties are supported. The default value comes from the CSS and varies based on theme.

svgClassName.description: The CSS style class defining the style of the item text.

value.description: The value of this item which will be used to scale its font-size within the tag cloud.

layout.description: The layout to use for tag display.

selection.description: An array containing the ids of the initially selected data items.

multiple.description: Multiple items can be selected at the same time.

none.description: Selection is disabled.

single.description: Only a single item can be selected at a time.

styleDefaults.description: An object defining the style defaults for this tag cloud.

animationDuration.description: The duration of the animations in milliseconds.

hoverBehaviorDelay.description: Specifies initial hover delay in milliseconds for highlighting data items.

svgStyle.description: The CSS style object defining the style of the items.

tooltip.description: An object containing an optional callback function for tooltip customization.

renderer.description: A function that returns a custom tooltip. The function takes a context argument, provided by the tag cloud. See the Help documentation for more information.

touchResponse.description: Specifies configuration options for touch and hold delays on mobile devices. See the Help documentation for more information.

trackResize.description: Defines whether the element will automatically render in response to changes in size. See the Help documentation for more information.

translations.description: A collection of translated resources from the translation bundle, or null if this component has no resources.

componentName.description: Used to describe the data visualization type for accessibility.

labelAndValue.description: Used to display a label and its value.

labelClearSelection.description: Text shown for clearing multiple selection on touch devices.

labelCountWithTotal.description: Used to display a count out of a total.

labelDataVisualization.description: Label for data visualizations used for accessibility.

labelInvalidData.description: Text shown when the component receives invalid data.

labelNoData.description: Text shown when the component receives no data.

stateCollapsed.description: Used to describe the collapsed state for accessibility.

stateDrillable.description: Used to describe a drillable object for accessibility.

stateExpanded.description: Used to describe the expanded state for accessibility.

stateHidden.description: Used to describe the hidden state for accessibility.

stateIsolated.description: Used to describe the isolated state for accessibility.

stateMaximized.description: Used to describe the maximized state for accessibility.

stateMinimized.description: Used to describe the minimized state for accessibility.

stateSelected.description: Used to describe the selected state for accessibility.

stateUnselected.description: Used to describe the unselected state for accessibility.

stateVisible.description: Used to describe the visible state for accessibility.

styleClasses.description: In the Redwood theme the default max width of a text field is 100%. These max width convenience classes are available to create a medium or small field.
In the Redwood theme the default width of a text field is 100%. These width convenience classes are available to create a medium or small field.
Classes that help align text of the element.
Changes the max-width to 100% so that form components will occupy all the available horizontal space.

styleClasses.name: form-control-max-width
styleClasses.description: In the Redwood theme the default max width of a text field is 100%. These max width convenience classes are available to create a medium or small field.

styleItems.name: oj-form-control-max-width-md
styleItems.description: Sets the max width for a medium field

styleClasses.description: In the Redwood theme the default width of a text field is 100%. These width convenience classes are available to create a medium or small field.

styleItems.description: Sets the width for a medium field

styleItems.description: Aligns the text to the right regardless of the reading direction. This is normally used for right aligning numbers.

styleItems.description: Aligns the text to the left in LTR and to the right in RTL.

styleItems.name: oj-form-control-text-align-end

oj-text-area.description: A text area allows the user to enter a multi-line text value.

status.description: Use the validators property instead for either regular Validators or AsyncValidators.

asyncValidators.description: Specifies a list of asynchronous validators used by the component when performing validation. Use async-validators when you need to perform some validation work on the server. See the Help documentation for more information.

autocomplete.description: Specifies a component's autocomplete state. See the Help documentation for more information.

autofocus.description: Specifies whether the component will get input focus when the page is loaded. See the Help documentation for more information.

status.description: Defining a converter with an object literal with converter type and its options (aka JSON format) has been deprecated and does nothing. If needed, you can make the JSON format work again by importing the deprecated module you need, like ojvalidation-base or ojvalidation-number module.

converter.description: An object that converts the value. See the Help documentation for more information.

describedBy.description: The form component's oj-label automatically sets described-by to make it accessible. It is not meant to be set by application developer.

disabled.description: Specifies whether the component is disabled. The default is false.

displayOptions.description: Display options for auxiliary content that determines whether or not it should be displayed.

converterHint.description: Display options for auxiliary converter hint text that determines whether it should be displayed.

status.description: If you want none, remove help-instruction attribute.

helpInstruction.description: Display options for auxiliary help instruction text that determines whether it should be displayed.

messages.description: Display options for auxiliary message text that determines whether it should be displayed.

validatorHint.description: Display options for auxiliary validator hint text that determines whether it should be displayed.

instruction.description: Represents advisory information for the component, such as would be appropriate for a tooltip.

helpHints.description: Represents hints for an oj-form-layout element to render help information on the label of the editable component.

definition.description: Hint for help definition text associated with the label.

source.description: Help source URL associated with the component.

labelEdge.description: Defines how the label of a component is created. See the Help documentation for more information.

inside.description: The component creates the label using the label-hint attribute.

none.description: The component will not have a label, regardless of whether it's in an oj-form-layout or not.

provided.description: Label is provided by the parent if the parent is an oj-form-layout.

labelHint.description: Represents a hint for oj-form-layout element to render a label on the editable component.

labelledBy.description: The oj-label sets the labelledBy property programmatically on the form component. See the Help documentation for more information.

length.description: An object whose properties describe the maximum length attributes.

countBy.description: Specifies the manner in which the text area characters has to be counted.

codePoint.description: Uses code point to calculate the text length

codeUnit.description: Uses code unit to calculate the text length

counter.description: The type of counter to display.

none.description: The remaining characters count is not displayed.

remaining.description: The remaining characters count is displayed.

max.description: Specifies the maximum number of characters to be entered in the text area.

maxRows.description: Specifies the maximum number of visible text lines of the textarea.

messagesCustom.description: A list of messages added by an application to the component. See the Help documentation for more information.

status.description: JET does not use form submit, so this is not needed.

name.description: Specifies the name of the component.

placeholder.description: The placeholder text to set on the element.

rawValue.description: Read-only property used for retrieving the current value from the input field in string form. See the Help documentation for more information.

readonly.description: Specifies whether the component is read-only. A read-only element cannot be modified, but user interaction is allowed. See the Help documentation for more information.

required.description: Specifies whether the component is required or optional. See the Help documentation for more information.

resizeBehavior.description: Specifies the resize behavior, based upon native browser support. See the Help documentation for more information.

both.description: The textarea will be interactively resizable horizontally and vertically.

horizontal.description: The textarea will be resizable in the horizontal direction only.

none.description: The textarea will not be interactively resizable.

vertical.description: The textarea will be resizable in the vertical direction only.

rows.description: Specifies the visible number of lines in the text area.

translations.description: A collection of translated resources from the translation bundle, or null if this component has no resources.

accessibleMaxLengthExceeded.description: Message to announce to AT via aria-live when the length.max is exceeded.

accessibleMaxLengthRemaining.description: Message to annnouce to AT via aria-live for the remaining character count.

regexp.description: Provides properties to customize the message text used by the implicit regexp validator associated to the InputText and TextArea components.

messageDetail.description: Provides properties to customize the error message detail used by the implicit regexp validator associated to the InputText and TextArea components.

messageSummary.description: Provides properties to customize the error message summary used by the implicit regexp validator associated to the InputText and TextArea components.

required.description: Provides properties to customize the summary, detail and hint text used by the implicit required validator associated to any editable component that supports the required option.

hint.description: Hint text used by required validation error.

messageDetail.description: Message text that describes the details of the required validation error.

messageSummary.description: Message text for summarizing a required validation error.

userAssistanceDensity.description: Specifies the density of the form component's user assistance presentation.

compact.description: Messages, help, hints, and required will not be shown inline; they will show in a mode that keeps the screen more compact, like a popup for the messages, and a required icon to indicate Required.

efficient.description: Messages, help, hints, and required are all shown inline under the field with reserved space.

reflow.description: Messages, help, hints, and required are all shown inline under the field with no reserved space.

valid.description: The validity state of the component

invalidHidden.description: The component has invalid messages hidden and no invalid messages showing. An invalid message is one with severity "error" or higher.

invalidShown.description: The component has invalid messages showing. An invalid message is one with severity "error" or higher.

pending.description: The component is waiting for the validation state to be determined. The "pending" state is set at the start of the convert/validate process.

valid.description: The component is valid

status.description: Defining a validator with an object literal with validator type and its options (aka JSON format) has been deprecated and does nothing. If needed, you can make the JSON format work again by importing the deprecated ojvalidation module you need, like ojvalidation-base.

validators.description: Specifies a list of synchronous validators for performing validation by the element. See the Help documentation for more information.

value.description: The value of the component.

validate.description: Validates the component's display value using all converters and validators registered on the component. If there are no validation errors. then the value is updated. See the Help documentation for more information.

reset.description: Resets the component by clearing all messages and messages attributes, and updates the component's display value using the attribute value.

showMessages.description: Takes all deferred messages and shows them.

setProperty.description: Sets a property or a single subproperty for complex properties and notifies the component of the change, triggering a corresponding event.

params.description: The property name to set. Supports dot notation for subproperty access.

params.description: The property name to get. Supports dot notation for subproperty access.

params.description: An object containing the property and value pairs to set.

ojAnimateStart.description: Triggered when a default animation is about to start, such as when the component is being opened/closed or a child item is being added/removed.

action.description: The action that triggers the animation.

endCallback.description: If the event listener calls event.preventDefault to cancel the default animation, it must call the endCallback function when it finishes its own animation handling and any custom animation has ended.

ojAnimateEnd.description: Triggered when a default animation has ended.

action.description: The action that triggered the animation.

contextMenu.description: The contextMenu slot is set on the oj-menu instance within this element. It designates the JET Menu to launch as a context menu.

oj-thematic-map-area.name: oj-thematic-map-area
oj-thematic-map-area.description: The oj-thematic-map-area element is used to declare properties for thematic map areas. See the Help documentation for more information.

categories.description: An array of category strings corresponding to this area. This allows highlighting and filtering of areas. By default, the label is used as the area category.

color.description: The area color.

label.description: Text used for the area's label.

labelStyle.description: The CSS style object defining the style of the area label.

location.description: An identifier corresponding to a mapProvider "Feature" geo object that this area is associated with.

selectable.description: Specifies whether or not the area will be selectable.

shortDesc.description: The text that displays in the area's tooltip.

svgClassName.description: The CSS style class defining the style of the area.

svgStyle.description: The CSS style object defining the style of the area. Only SVG CSS style properties are supported.

oj-thematic-map-link.name: oj-thematic-map-link
oj-thematic-map-link.description: The oj-thematic-map-link element is used to declare properties for thematic map links. See the Help documentation for more information.

categories.description: An array of category strings corresponding to this link. This allows highlighting and filtering of links. By default, the label is used as the link category.

color.description: The link color.

endLocation.description: An object used to determine the end point of the link.

id.description: The marker or area id to be used as the end point.

location.description: An identifier corresponding to a mapProvider "Feature" geo object to be used as the end point.

x.description: The x coordinate which can represent latitude of the end point.

y.description: The y coordinate which can represent longitude of the end point.

selectable.description: Specifies whether or not the link will be selectable.

shortDesc.description: The text that displays in the link's tooltip.

startLocation.description: An object used to determine the start point of the link.

id.description: The marker or area id to be used as the start point.

location.description: An identifier corresponding to a mapProvider "Feature" geo object to be used as the start point.

x.description: The x coordinate which can represent latitude of the start point.

y.description: The y coordinate which can represent longitude of the start point.

svgClassName.description: The CSS style class defining the style of the link.

svgStyle.description: The CSS style object defining the style of the link. Only SVG CSS style properties are supported.

width.description: The link width in pixels.

oj-thematic-map-marker.name: oj-thematic-map-marker
oj-thematic-map-marker.description: The oj-thematic-map-marker element is used to declare properties for thematic map markers. See the Help documentation for more information.

borderColor.description: The marker border color.

borderWidth.description: The marker border width in pixels.

categories.description: An array of category strings corresponding to this marker. This allows highlighting and filtering of markers. By default, the label is used as the marker category.

color.description: The marker color.

height.description: The marker height in pixels.

label.description: Text used for the marker's label.

labelPosition.description: Determines the label position relative to the marker.

labelStyle.description: The CSS style object defining the style of the marker label.

location.description: An identifier corresponding to a mapProvider "Feature" geo object that this marker is associated with.

rotation.description: The angle in degrees to rotate the marker clockwise around the marker center.

selectable.description: Specifies whether or not the marker will be selectable.

shape.description: Specifies the shape of a marker. Can take the name of a built-in shape or the SVG path commands for a custom shape.

shortDesc.description: The text that displays in the marker's tooltip.

source.description: Specifies a URI for the location of the image resource to use for the marker instead of a built-in shape. The shape attribute is ignored if the source image is defined.

sourceHover.description: An optional URI for the location of the hover image resource. If not defined, the source image will be used.

sourceHoverSelected.description: An optional URI for the location of the selected image resource on hover. See the Help documentation for more information.

sourceSelected.description: An optional URI for the location of the selected image. If not defined, the source image will be used.

svgClassName.description: The CSS style class defining the style of the marker.

svgStyle.description: The CSS style object defining the style of the marker. Only SVG CSS style properties are supported.

value.description: A data value used to calculate the marker dimensions. See the Help documentation for more information.

width.description: The marker width in pixels.

x.description: The x coordinate of the marker transformed using the map projection, which can be null if location is set instead.

y.description: The y coordinate of the marker transformed using the map projection, which can be null if location is set instead.

oj-thematic-map.name: oj-thematic-map
oj-thematic-map.description: A thematic map is an interactive data visualization that displays data corresponding to geographic locations or regions.             Applications are required to supply a mapProvider for a valid thematic map.

animationDuration.description: The duration of the animations in milliseconds. See the Help documentation for more information.

animationOnDisplay.description: Specifies the animation that is shown on initial display.

areaData.description: Specifies the DataProvider for the areas of the thematic map. See the Help documentation for more information.

areas.description: An array of objects that define area data layers. Also accepts a Promise for deferred data rendering. See the Help documentation for more information.

categories.description: An array of category strings corresponding to this area. This allows highlighting and filtering of areas.

color.description: The area color.

id.description: The identifier for this area. The id should be set by the application if the DataProvider is not being used. The row key will be used as id in the case.

label.description: Text used for the area's label.

labelStyle.description: The CSS style defining the label style for this area. The following style properties are supported: color, cursor, fontFamily, fontSize, fontStyle, fontWeight, textDecoration.

location.description: An identifier corresponding to a Feature provided in the mapProvider geo object that this area is associated with.

selectable.description: Specifies whether or not the area will be selectable.

shortDesc.description: The text that displays in the area's tooltip.

svgClassName.description: The CSS style class defining the style of the area.

svgStyle.description: The CSS style object defining the style of the area. Only SVG CSS style properties are supported.

status.description: Set the alias directly on the template element using the data-oj-as attribute instead.

as.description: An alias for the '$current' context variable passed to slot content for the areaTemplate, markerTemplate, or linkTemplate slots.

focusRenderer.description: An optional callback function to update the data item in response to changes in keyboard focus state. The function takes a context argument, provided by the thematic map. See the Help documentation for more information.

hiddenCategories.description: An array of category strings used for filtering. Data items matching categories in this array will be filtered.

highlightMatch.description: The matching condition for the highlightedCategories property. See the Help documentation for more information.

highlightedCategories.description: An array of category strings used for highlighting. Data items matching categories in this array will be highlighted.

hoverBehavior.description: Defines the behavior applied when hovering over data items.

hoverRenderer.description: An optional callback function to update the node in response to changes in hover state. The function takes a context argument, provided by the thematic map. See the Help documentation for more information.

initialZooming.description: Specifies whether the map will zoom to fit the data objects on initial render.

isolatedItem.description: The id for the isolated area of this area data layer. If set, only the isolated area will be displayed.

labelDisplay.description: Specifies how labels for this layer should be displayed.

auto.description: Renders the label if it fits within the area bounds.

labelType.description: Specifies which type of map labels to display.

animationDuration.description: Specifies the animation duration in milliseconds. For data change animations with multiple stages, the value specifies the duration of each stage.

animationOnDataChange.description: Specifies the animation that is applied on data changes.

animationOnDisplay.description: Specifies the animation that is shown on initial display.

animationUpdateColor.description: Specifies the color displayed during a data change animation when a node is updated.

status.description: Set the alias directly on the template element using the data-oj-as attribute instead.

colorLabel.description: Specifies the label displayed in the legend describing the color metric of the treemap.

displayLevels.description: The number of levels of nodes to display. By default all nodes are displayed.

groupGaps.description: Specifies whether gaps are displayed between groups. Gaps can be useful for drawing attention to the differences between groups.

highlightMatch.description: The matching condition for the highlightedCategories property. See the Help documentation for more information.

oj-validation-group.name: oj-validation-group
oj-validation-group.description: A validation group tracks and summarizes the current validity state of a group of components.

valid.description: Read-only property used for retrieving the current validity state of the group of components being tracked. See the Help documentation for more information.

invalidHidden.description: The component has invalid messages hidden and no invalid messages showing. An invalid message is one with severity "error" or higher.

invalidShown.description: The component has invalid messages showing. An invalid message is one with severity "error" or higher.

pending.description: The component is waiting for the validation state to be determined. The "pending" state is never set in this release of JET. It will be set in a future release.

valid.description: The component is valid

setProperty.description: Sets a property or a single subproperty for complex properties and notifies the component of the change, triggering a corresponding event.

params.name: property
params.description: The property name to set. Supports dot notation for subproperty access.

params.name: value
params.description: The new value to set the property to.

getProperty.description: Retrieves a value for a property or a single subproperty for complex properties.

params.name: property
params.description: The property name to get. Supports dot notation for subproperty access.

setProperties.description: Performs a batch set of properties.

params.name: properties
params.description: An object containing the property and value pairs to set.

showMessages.description: Takes all deferred messages and shows them on each enabled component. An enabled component is one that is not disabled or readonly. As a result, the valid property may be updated; e.g., if the valid state was "invalidHidden" before showMessages(), the valid state will become "invalidShown" after showMessages().

focusOn.description: Sets the focus on one of the enabled components that is being tracked. See the Help documentation for more information.

params.name: key
params.description: "@firstInvalidShown" will focus on first invalidShown enabled component in DOM order, if any. When no parameter is passed in, the method will focus on first enabled component regardless of the valid state, if any. An enabled component is one that is not disabled or readonly.

slots.description: The <oj-validation-group> accepts any DOM elements in its Default slot but only tracks the validity state of any JET custom element descendents that contain the valid property.

scroller.description: The element used to determine the scroll position as well as the maximum scroll position. See the Help documentation for more information.
